--   Constraints:
--   
--   <ul>

--   <li>First character must be a letter</li>
--   <li>Cannot end with a hyphen or contain two consecutive hyphens</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   This value is stored as a lowercase string.
newDBClusterParameterGroupNameMessage :: DBClusterParameterGroupNameMessage

-- | The name of the DB cluster parameter group.

module Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBClusterRole

-- | Describes an Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM) role that is
--   associated with a DB cluster.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDBClusterRole</a> smart constructor.
data DBClusterRole
DBClusterRole' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> DBClusterRole

-- | Describes the state of association between the IAM role and the DB
--   cluster. The Status property returns one of the following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>ACTIVE</tt> - the IAM role ARN is associated with the DB
--   cluster and can be used to access other Amazon services on your
--   behalf.</li>
--   <li><tt>PENDING</tt> - the IAM role ARN is being associated with the
--   DB cluster.</li>
--   <li><tt>INVALID</tt> - the IAM role ARN is associated with the DB
--   cluster, but the DB cluster is unable to assume the IAM role in order
--   to access other Amazon services on your behalf.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:status:DBClusterRole'] :: DBClusterRole -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the feature associated with the Amazon Identity and Access
--   Management (IAM) role. For the list of supported feature names, see
--   DBEngineVersion.
[$sel:featureName:DBClusterRole'] :: DBClusterRole -> Maybe Text

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the IAM role that is associated with
--   the DB cluster.
[$sel:roleArn:DBClusterRole'] :: DBClusterRole -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>DBClusterRole</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:DBClusterRole'</a>, <a>dbClusterRole_status</a> -
--   Describes the state of association between the IAM role and the DB
--   cluster. The Status property returns one of the following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>ACTIVE</tt> - the IAM role ARN is associated with the DB
--   cluster and can be used to access other Amazon services on your
--   behalf.</li>
--   <li><tt>PENDING</tt> - the IAM role ARN is being associated with the
--   DB cluster.</li>
--   <li><tt>INVALID</tt> - the IAM role ARN is associated with the DB
--   cluster, but the DB cluster is unable to assume the IAM role in order
--   to access other Amazon services on your behalf.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:featureName:DBClusterRole'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterRole_featureName</a> - The name of the feature associated
--   with the Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM) role. For the
--   list of supported feature names, see DBEngineVersion.
--   
--   <a>$sel:roleArn:DBClusterRole'</a>, <a>dbClusterRole_roleArn</a> - The
--   Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the IAM role that is associated with the
--   DB cluster.
newDBClusterRole :: DBClusterRole

-- | Describes the state of association between the IAM role and the DB
--   cluster. The Status property returns one of the following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>ACTIVE</tt> - the IAM role ARN is associated with the DB
--   cluster and can be used to access other Amazon services on your
--   behalf.</li>
--   <li><tt>PENDING</tt> - the IAM role ARN is being associated with the
--   DB cluster.</li>
--   <li><tt>INVALID</tt> - the IAM role ARN is associated with the DB
--   cluster, but the DB cluster is unable to assume the IAM role in order
--   to access other Amazon services on your behalf.</li>
--   </ul>
dbClusterRole_status :: Lens' DBClusterRole (Maybe Text)

--   Management (IAM) role. For the list of supported feature names, see
--   DBEngineVersion.
dbClusterRole_featureName :: Lens' DBClusterRole (Maybe Text)

--   the DB cluster.
dbClusterRole_roleArn :: Lens' DBClusterRole (Maybe Text)

module Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBClusterSnapshot

-- | Contains the details for an Amazon Neptune DB cluster snapshot
--   
--   This data type is used as a response element in the
--   DescribeDBClusterSnapshots action.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDBClusterSnapshot</a> smart constructor.
data DBClusterSnapshot
DBClusterSnapshot' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> DBClusterSnapshot

-- | Provides the version of the database engine for this DB cluster
--   snapshot.
[$sel:engineVersion:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the status of this DB cluster snapshot.
[$sel:status:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies whether the DB cluster snapshot is encrypted.
[$sel:storageEncrypted:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specifies the DB cluster identifier of the DB cluster that this DB
--   cluster snapshot was created from.
[$sel:dbClusterIdentifier:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
[$sel:masterUsername:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | True if mapping of Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM)
--   accounts to database accounts is enabled, and otherwise false.
[$sel:iAMDatabaseAuthenticationEnabled:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Bool

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the DB cluster snapshot.
[$sel:dbClusterSnapshotArn:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides the VPC ID associated with the DB cluster snapshot.
[$sel:vpcId:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the identifier for a DB cluster snapshot. Must match the
--   identifier of an existing snapshot.
--   
--   After you restore a DB cluster using a
--   <tt>DBClusterSnapshotIdentifier</tt>, you must specify the same
--   <tt>DBClusterSnapshotIdentifier</tt> for any future updates to the DB
--   cluster. When you specify this property for an update, the DB cluster
--   is not restored from the snapshot again, and the data in the database
--   is not changed.
--   
--   However, if you don't specify the
--   <tt>DBClusterSnapshotIdentifier</tt>, an empty DB cluster is created,
--   and the original DB cluster is deleted. If you specify a property that
--   is different from the previous snapshot restore property, the DB
--   cluster is restored from the snapshot specified by the
--   <tt>DBClusterSnapshotIdentifier</tt>, and the original DB cluster is
--   deleted.
[$sel:dbClusterSnapshotIdentifier:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the name of the database engine.
[$sel:engine:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides the license model information for this DB cluster snapshot.
[$sel:licenseModel:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides the list of EC2 Availability Zones that instances in the DB
--   cluster snapshot can be restored in.
[$sel:availabilityZones:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe [Text]

-- | Provides the type of the DB cluster snapshot.
[$sel:snapshotType:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | If <tt>StorageEncrypted</tt> is true, the Amazon KMS key identifier
--   for the encrypted DB cluster snapshot.
[$sel:kmsKeyId:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides the time when the snapshot was taken, in Universal
--   Coordinated Time (UTC).
[$sel:snapshotCreateTime:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | Specifies the allocated storage size in gibibytes (GiB).
[$sel:allocatedStorage:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Int

-- | If the DB cluster snapshot was copied from a source DB cluster
--   snapshot, the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the source DB cluster
--   snapshot, otherwise, a null value.
[$sel:sourceDBClusterSnapshotArn:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the time when the DB cluster was created, in Universal
--   Coordinated Time (UTC).
[$sel:clusterCreateTime:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | Specifies the percentage of the estimated data that has been
--   transferred.
[$sel:percentProgress:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Int

-- | Specifies the port that the DB cluster was listening on at the time of
--   the snapshot.
[$sel:port:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Int

-- | Create a value of <a>DBClusterSnapshot</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:engineVersion:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshot_engineVersion</a> - Provides the version of the
--   database engine for this DB cluster snapshot.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>, <a>dbClusterSnapshot_status</a>
--   - Specifies the status of this DB cluster snapshot.
--   
--   <a>$sel:storageEncrypted:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshot_storageEncrypted</a> - Specifies whether the DB
--   cluster snapshot is encrypted.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbClusterIdentifier:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshot_dbClusterIdentifier</a> - Specifies the DB
--   cluster identifier of the DB cluster that this DB cluster snapshot was
--   created from.
--   
--   <a>$sel:masterUsername:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshot_masterUsername</a> - Not supported by Neptune.

module Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBClusterSnapshotAttribute

-- | Contains the name and values of a manual DB cluster snapshot
--   attribute.
--   
--   Manual DB cluster snapshot attributes are used to authorize other
--   Amazon accounts to restore a manual DB cluster snapshot. For more
--   information, see the ModifyDBClusterSnapshotAttribute API action.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDBClusterSnapshotAttribute</a> smart constructor.
data DBClusterSnapshotAttribute
DBClusterSnapshotAttribute' :: Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> DBClusterSnapshotAttribute

-- | The value(s) for the manual DB cluster snapshot attribute.
--   
--   If the <tt>AttributeName</tt> field is set to <tt>restore</tt>, then
--   this element returns a list of IDs of the Amazon accounts that are
--   authorized to copy or restore the manual DB cluster snapshot. If a
--   value of <tt>all</tt> is in the list, then the manual DB cluster
--   snapshot is public and available for any Amazon account to copy or
--   restore.
[$sel:attributeValues:DBClusterSnapshotAttribute'] :: DBClusterSnapshotAttribute -> Maybe [Text]

-- | The name of the manual DB cluster snapshot attribute.
--   
--   The attribute named <tt>restore</tt> refers to the list of Amazon
--   accounts that have permission to copy or restore the manual DB cluster
--   snapshot. For more information, see the
--   ModifyDBClusterSnapshotAttribute API action.
[$sel:attributeName:DBClusterSnapshotAttribute'] :: DBClusterSnapshotAttribute -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>DBClusterSnapshotAttribute</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:attributeValues:DBClusterSnapshotAttribute'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshotAttribute_attributeValues</a> - The value(s) for
--   the manual DB cluster snapshot attribute.
--   
--   If the <tt>AttributeName</tt> field is set to <tt>restore</tt>, then
--   this element returns a list of IDs of the Amazon accounts that are
--   authorized to copy or restore the manual DB cluster snapshot. If a
--   value of <tt>all</tt> is in the list, then the manual DB cluster
--   snapshot is public and available for any Amazon account to copy or
--   restore.
--   
--   <a>$sel:attributeName:DBClusterSnapshotAttribute'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshotAttribute_attributeName</a> - The name of the
--   manual DB cluster snapshot attribute.
--   
--   The attribute named <tt>restore</tt> refers to the list of Amazon
--   accounts that have permission to copy or restore the manual DB cluster
--   snapshot. For more information, see the
--   ModifyDBClusterSnapshotAttribute API action.
newDBClusterSnapshotAttribute :: DBClusterSnapshotAttribute

-- | The value(s) for the manual DB cluster snapshot attribute.
--   
--   If the <tt>AttributeName</tt> field is set to <tt>restore</tt>, then
--   this element returns a list of IDs of the Amazon accounts that are
--   authorized to copy or restore the manual DB cluster snapshot. If a

--   snapshot is public and available for any Amazon account to copy or
--   restore.
dbClusterSnapshotAttribute_attributeValues :: Lens' DBClusterSnapshotAttribute (Maybe [Text])

module Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBClusterSnapshotAttributesResult

--   DescribeDBClusterSnapshotAttributes API action.

module Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBInstanceStatusInfo

-- | Provides a list of status information for a DB instance.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDBInstanceStatusInfo</a> smart constructor.
data DBInstanceStatusInfo
DBInstanceStatusInfo' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> DBInstanceStatusInfo

-- | Status of the DB instance. For a StatusType of read replica, the
--   values can be replicating, error, stopped, or terminated.
[$sel:status:DBInstanceStatusInfo'] :: DBInstanceStatusInfo -> Maybe Text

-- | Boolean value that is true if the instance is operating normally, or
--   false if the instance is in an error state.
[$sel:normal:DBInstanceStatusInfo'] :: DBInstanceStatusInfo -> Maybe Bool

-- | This value is currently "read replication."
[$sel:statusType:DBInstanceStatusInfo'] :: DBInstanceStatusInfo -> Maybe Text

-- | Details of the error if there is an error for the instance. If the
--   instance is not in an error state, this value is blank.
[$sel:message:DBInstanceStatusInfo'] :: DBInstanceStatusInfo -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>DBInstanceStatusInfo</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:DBInstanceStatusInfo'</a>,
--   <a>dbInstanceStatusInfo_status</a> - Status of the DB instance. For a
--   StatusType of read replica, the values can be replicating, error,
--   stopped, or terminated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:normal:DBInstanceStatusInfo'</a>,
--   <a>dbInstanceStatusInfo_normal</a> - Boolean value that is true if the
--   instance is operating normally, or false if the instance is in an
--   error state.
--   
--   <a>$sel:statusType:DBInstanceStatusInfo'</a>,
--   <a>dbInstanceStatusInfo_statusType</a> - This value is currently "read
--   replication."
--   
--   <a>$sel:message:DBInstanceStatusInfo'</a>,
--   <a>dbInstanceStatusInfo_message</a> - Details of the error if there is
--   an error for the instance. If the instance is not in an error state,
--   this value is blank.
newDBInstanceStatusInfo :: DBInstanceStatusInfo

-- | Status of the DB instance. For a StatusType of read replica, the
--   values can be replicating, error, stopped, or terminated.
dbInstanceStatusInfo_status :: Lens' DBInstanceStatusInfo (Maybe Text)

-- | Boolean value that is true if the instance is operating normally, or
--   false if the instance is in an error state.
dbInstanceStatusInfo_normal :: Lens' DBInstanceStatusInfo (Maybe Bool)

-- | This value is currently "read replication."
dbInstanceStatusInfo_statusType :: Lens' DBInstanceStatusInfo (Maybe Text)

-- | Details of the error if there is an error for the instance. If the
--   instance is not in an error state, this value is blank.
dbInstanceStatusInfo_message :: Lens' DBInstanceStatusInfo (Maybe Text)

instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBInstanceStatusInfo.DBInstanceStatusInfo

module Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.EventSubscription

-- | Contains the results of a successful invocation of the
--   DescribeEventSubscriptions action.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newEventSubscription</a> smart constructor.
data EventSubscription
EventSubscription' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe [Text] -> EventSubscription

-- | The status of the event notification subscription.
--   
--   Constraints:
--   
--   Can be one of the following: creating | modifying | deleting | active
--   | no-permission | topic-not-exist
--   
--   The status "no-permission" indicates that Neptune no longer has
--   permission to post to the SNS topic. The status "topic-not-exist"
--   indicates that the topic was deleted after the subscription was
--   created.
[$sel:status:EventSubscription'] :: EventSubscription -> Maybe Text

-- | The Amazon customer account associated with the event notification
--   subscription.
[$sel:customerAwsId:EventSubscription'] :: EventSubscription -> Maybe Text

-- | The event notification subscription Id.
[$sel:custSubscriptionId:EventSubscription'] :: EventSubscription -> Maybe Text

-- | The topic ARN of the event notification subscription.
[$sel:snsTopicArn:EventSubscription'] :: EventSubscription -> Maybe Text

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the event subscription.
[$sel:eventSubscriptionArn:EventSubscription'] :: EventSubscription -> Maybe Text

-- | A Boolean value indicating if the subscription is enabled. True
--   indicates the subscription is enabled.
[$sel:enabled:EventSubscription'] :: EventSubscription -> Maybe Bool

-- | The source type for the event notification subscription.
[$sel:sourceType:EventSubscription'] :: EventSubscription -> Maybe Text

-- | The time the event notification subscription was created.
[$sel:subscriptionCreationTime:EventSubscription'] :: EventSubscription -> Maybe Text

-- | A list of event categories for the event notification subscription.
[$sel:eventCategoriesList:EventSubscription'] :: EventSubscription -> Maybe [Text]

-- | A list of source IDs for the event notification subscription.
[$sel:sourceIdsList:EventSubscription'] :: EventSubscription -> Maybe [Text]

-- | Create a value of <a>EventSubscription</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:EventSubscription'</a>, <a>eventSubscription_status</a>
--   - The status of the event notification subscription.
--   
--   Constraints:
--   
--   Can be one of the following: creating | modifying | deleting | active
--   | no-permission | topic-not-exist
--   
--   The status "no-permission" indicates that Neptune no longer has
--   permission to post to the SNS topic. The status "topic-not-exist"
--   indicates that the topic was deleted after the subscription was
--   created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:customerAwsId:EventSubscription'</a>,
--   <a>eventSubscription_customerAwsId</a> - The Amazon customer account
--   associated with the event notification subscription.
--   
--   <a>$sel:custSubscriptionId:EventSubscription'</a>,
--   <a>eventSubscription_custSubscriptionId</a> - The event notification
--   subscription Id.
--   
--   <a>$sel:snsTopicArn:EventSubscription'</a>,
--   <a>eventSubscription_snsTopicArn</a> - The topic ARN of the event
--   notification subscription.
--   
--   <a>$sel:eventSubscriptionArn:EventSubscription'</a>,
--   <a>eventSubscription_eventSubscriptionArn</a> - The Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) for the event subscription.
--   
--   <a>$sel:enabled:EventSubscription'</a>,
--   <a>eventSubscription_enabled</a> - A Boolean value indicating if the
--   subscription is enabled. True indicates the subscription is enabled.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceType:EventSubscription'</a>,
--   <a>eventSubscription_sourceType</a> - The source type for the event
--   notification subscription.
--   
--   <a>$sel:subscriptionCreationTime:EventSubscription'</a>,
--   <a>eventSubscription_subscriptionCreationTime</a> - The time the event
--   notification subscription was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:eventCategoriesList:EventSubscription'</a>,
--   <a>eventSubscription_eventCategoriesList</a> - A list of event
--   categories for the event notification subscription.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceIdsList:EventSubscription'</a>,
--   <a>eventSubscription_sourceIdsList</a> - A list of source IDs for the
--   event notification subscription.
newEventSubscription :: EventSubscription

-- | The status of the event notification subscription.
--   
--   Constraints:
--   
--   Can be one of the following: creating | modifying | deleting | active
--   | no-permission | topic-not-exist
--   
--   The status "no-permission" indicates that Neptune no longer has
--   permission to post to the SNS topic. The status "topic-not-exist"
--   indicates that the topic was deleted after the subscription was
--   created.
eventSubscription_status :: Lens' EventSubscription (Maybe Text)

-- | The Amazon customer account associated with the event notification
--   subscription.
eventSubscription_customerAwsId :: Lens' EventSubscription (Maybe Text)

-- | The event notification subscription Id.
eventSubscription_custSubscriptionId :: Lens' EventSubscription (Maybe Text)

-- | The topic ARN of the event notification subscription.
eventSubscription_snsTopicArn :: Lens' EventSubscription (Maybe Text)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the event subscription.
eventSubscription_eventSubscriptionArn :: Lens' EventSubscription (Maybe Text)

-- | A Boolean value indicating if the subscription is enabled. True
--   indicates the subscription is enabled.
eventSubscription_enabled :: Lens' EventSubscription (Maybe Bool)

-- | The source type for the event notification subscription.
eventSubscription_sourceType :: Lens' EventSubscription (Maybe Text)

-- | The time the event notification subscription was created.
eventSubscription_subscriptionCreationTime :: Lens' EventSubscription (Maybe Text)

-- | A list of event categories for the event notification subscription.
eventSubscription_eventCategoriesList :: Lens' EventSubscription (Maybe [Text])

-- | A list of source IDs for the event notification subscription.
eventSubscription_sourceIdsList :: Lens' EventSubscription (Maybe [Text])
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.EventSubscription.EventSubscription
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.EventSubscription.EventSubscription
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.EventSubscription.EventSubscription
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.EventSubscription.EventSubscription
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.EventSubscription.EventSubscription
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.EventSubscription.EventSubscription
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.EventSubscription.EventSubscription

-- | Contains a list of available options for a DB instance.
--   
--   This data type is used as a response element in the
--   DescribeOrderableDBInstanceOptions action.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newOrderableDBInstanceOption</a> smart constructor.
data OrderableDBInstanceOption
OrderableDBInstanceOption' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Double -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [AvailabilityZone] -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Double -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> OrderableDBInstanceOption

-- | The engine version of a DB instance.
[$sel:engineVersion:OrderableDBInstanceOption'] :: OrderableDBInstanceOption -> Maybe Text

-- | Minimum provisioned IOPS per GiB for a DB instance.
[$sel:minIopsPerGib:OrderableDBInstanceOption'] :: OrderableDBInstanceOption -> Maybe Double

-- | Indicates whether a DB instance supports IAM database authentication.
[$sel:supportsIAMDatabaseAuthentication:OrderableDBInstanceOption'] :: OrderableDBInstanceOption -> Maybe Bool

-- | Minimum total provisioned IOPS for a DB instance.
[$sel:minIopsPerDbInstance:OrderableDBInstanceOption'] :: OrderableDBInstanceOption -> Maybe Int

-- | Indicates whether a DB instance is Multi-AZ capable.
[$sel:multiAZCapable:OrderableDBInstanceOption'] :: OrderableDBInstanceOption -> Maybe Bool

-- | Maximum storage size for a DB instance.
[$sel:maxStorageSize:OrderableDBInstanceOption'] :: OrderableDBInstanceOption -> Maybe Int

-- | The engine type of a DB instance.
[$sel:engine:OrderableDBInstanceOption'] :: OrderableDBInstanceOption -> Maybe Text

-- | Minimum storage size for a DB instance.
[$sel:minStorageSize:OrderableDBInstanceOption'] :: OrderableDBInstanceOption -> Maybe Int

-- | Indicates whether a DB instance supports provisioned IOPS.
[$sel:supportsIops:OrderableDBInstanceOption'] :: OrderableDBInstanceOption -> Maybe Bool

-- | <i>(Not supported by Neptune)</i>
[$sel:supportsPerformanceInsights:OrderableDBInstanceOption'] :: OrderableDBInstanceOption -> Maybe Bool

-- | The DB instance class for a DB instance.
[$sel:dbInstanceClass:OrderableDBInstanceOption'] :: OrderableDBInstanceOption -> Maybe Text

-- | The license model for a DB instance.

[$sel:supportsStorageEncryption:OrderableDBInstanceOption'] :: OrderableDBInstanceOption -> Maybe Bool

-- | Indicates whether a DB instance can have a Read Replica.
[$sel:readReplicaCapable:OrderableDBInstanceOption'] :: OrderableDBInstanceOption -> Maybe Bool

[$sel:vpc:OrderableDBInstanceOption'] :: OrderableDBInstanceOption -> Maybe Bool

--   intervals from 1 to 60 seconds.
[$sel:supportsEnhancedMonitoring:OrderableDBInstanceOption'] :: OrderableDBInstanceOption -> Maybe Bool

module Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Parameter

-- | Specifies a parameter.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newParameter</a> smart constructor.
data Parameter
Parameter' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ApplyMethod -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Parameter

-- | Specifies the engine specific parameters type.
[$sel:applyType:Parameter'] :: Parameter -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the value of the parameter.
[$sel:parameterValue:Parameter'] :: Parameter -> Maybe Text

-- | Indicates when to apply parameter updates.
[$sel:applyMethod:Parameter'] :: Parameter -> Maybe ApplyMethod

-- | The earliest engine version to which the parameter can apply.
[$sel:minimumEngineVersion:Parameter'] :: Parameter -> Maybe Text

-- | Indicates the source of the parameter value.
[$sel:source:Parameter'] :: Parameter -> Maybe Text

-- | Indicates whether (<tt>true</tt>) or not (<tt>false</tt>) the
--   parameter can be modified. Some parameters have security or
--   operational implications that prevent them from being changed.
[$sel:isModifiable:Parameter'] :: Parameter -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specifies the valid data type for the parameter.
[$sel:dataType:Parameter'] :: Parameter -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the valid range of values for the parameter.
[$sel:allowedValues:Parameter'] :: Parameter -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the name of the parameter.
[$sel:parameterName:Parameter'] :: Parameter -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides a description of the parameter.
[$sel:description:Parameter'] :: Parameter -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>Parameter</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:applyType:Parameter'</a>, <a>parameter_applyType</a> -
--   Specifies the engine specific parameters type.
--   
--   <a>$sel:parameterValue:Parameter'</a>, <a>parameter_parameterValue</a>
--   - Specifies the value of the parameter.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applyMethod:Parameter'</a>, <a>parameter_applyMethod</a> -
--   Indicates when to apply parameter updates.
--   
--   <a>$sel:minimumEngineVersion:Parameter'</a>,
--   <a>parameter_minimumEngineVersion</a> - The earliest engine version to
--   which the parameter can apply.
--   
--   <a>$sel:source:Parameter'</a>, <a>parameter_source</a> - Indicates the
--   source of the parameter value.
--   
--   <a>$sel:isModifiable:Parameter'</a>, <a>parameter_isModifiable</a> -
--   Indicates whether (<tt>true</tt>) or not (<tt>false</tt>) the
--   parameter can be modified. Some parameters have security or
--   operational implications that prevent them from being changed.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataType:Parameter'</a>, <a>parameter_dataType</a> - Specifies
--   the valid data type for the parameter.
--   
--   <a>$sel:allowedValues:Parameter'</a>, <a>parameter_allowedValues</a> -
--   Specifies the valid range of values for the parameter.
--   
--   <a>$sel:parameterName:Parameter'</a>, <a>parameter_parameterName</a> -
--   Specifies the name of the parameter.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:Parameter'</a>, <a>parameter_description</a> -
--   Provides a description of the parameter.
newParameter :: Parameter

-- | Specifies the engine specific parameters type.
parameter_applyType :: Lens' Parameter (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the value of the parameter.
parameter_parameterValue :: Lens' Parameter (Maybe Text)

-- | Indicates when to apply parameter updates.
parameter_applyMethod :: Lens' Parameter (Maybe ApplyMethod)

-- | The earliest engine version to which the parameter can apply.
parameter_minimumEngineVersion :: Lens' Parameter (Maybe Text)

-- | Indicates the source of the parameter value.
parameter_source :: Lens' Parameter (Maybe Text)

-- | Indicates whether (<tt>true</tt>) or not (<tt>false</tt>) the
--   parameter can be modified. Some parameters have security or
--   operational implications that prevent them from being changed.
parameter_isModifiable :: Lens' Parameter (Maybe Bool)

-- | Specifies the valid data type for the parameter.
parameter_dataType :: Lens' Parameter (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the valid range of values for the parameter.
parameter_allowedValues :: Lens' Parameter (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the name of the parameter.
parameter_parameterName :: Lens' Parameter (Maybe Text)

-- | Provides a description of the parameter.
parameter_description :: Lens' Parameter (Maybe Text)

instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Parameter.Parameter
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Parameter.Parameter

module Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.EngineDefaults

-- | Contains the result of a successful invocation of the
--   DescribeEngineDefaultParameters action.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newEngineDefaults</a> smart constructor.
data EngineDefaults
EngineDefaults' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Parameter] -> EngineDefaults

-- | Specifies the name of the DB parameter group family that the engine
--   default parameters apply to.
[$sel:dbParameterGroupFamily:EngineDefaults'] :: EngineDefaults -> Maybe Text

-- | An optional pagination token provided by a previous EngineDefaults
--   request. If this parameter is specified, the response includes only
--   records beyond the marker, up to the value specified by
--   <tt>MaxRecords</tt> .
[$sel:marker:EngineDefaults'] :: EngineDefaults -> Maybe Text

[$sel:parameters:EngineDefaults'] :: EngineDefaults -> Maybe [Parameter]

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   the DB parameter group family that the engine default parameters apply
--   to.
--   
--   <a>$sel:marker:EngineDefaults'</a>, <a>engineDefaults_marker</a> - An
--   optional pagination token provided by a previous EngineDefaults
--   request. If this parameter is specified, the response includes only
--   records beyond the marker, up to the value specified by
--   <tt>MaxRecords</tt> .
--   
--   <a>$sel:parameters:EngineDefaults'</a>,
--   <a>engineDefaults_parameters</a> - Contains a list of engine default
--   parameters.
newEngineDefaults :: EngineDefaults

-- | Specifies the name of the DB parameter group family that the engine
--   default parameters apply to.

--   request. If this parameter is specified, the response includes only
--   records beyond the marker, up to the value specified by
--   <tt>MaxRecords</tt> .

module Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.PendingCloudwatchLogsExports

-- | A list of the log types whose configuration is still pending. In other
--   words, these log types are in the process of being activated or
--   deactivated.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newPendingCloudwatchLogsExports</a> smart constructor.
data PendingCloudwatchLogsExports
PendingCloudwatchLogsExports' :: Maybe [Text] -> Maybe [Text] -> PendingCloudwatchLogsExports

-- | Log types that are in the process of being deactivated. After they are
--   deactivated, these log types aren't exported to CloudWatch Logs.
[$sel:logTypesToEnable:PendingCloudwatchLogsExports'] :: PendingCloudwatchLogsExports -> Maybe [Text]

-- | Log types that are in the process of being enabled. After they are
--   enabled, these log types are exported to CloudWatch Logs.
[$sel:logTypesToDisable:PendingCloudwatchLogsExports'] :: PendingCloudwatchLogsExports -> Maybe [Text]

-- | Create a value of <a>PendingCloudwatchLogsExports</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:logTypesToEnable:PendingCloudwatchLogsExports'</a>,
--   <a>pendingCloudwatchLogsExports_logTypesToEnable</a> - Log types that
--   are in the process of being deactivated. After they are deactivated,
--   these log types aren't exported to CloudWatch Logs.
--   
--   <a>$sel:logTypesToDisable:PendingCloudwatchLogsExports'</a>,
--   <a>pendingCloudwatchLogsExports_logTypesToDisable</a> - Log types that
--   are in the process of being enabled. After they are enabled, these log
--   types are exported to CloudWatch Logs.
newPendingCloudwatchLogsExports :: PendingCloudwatchLogsExports

-- | Log types that are in the process of being deactivated. After they are
--   deactivated, these log types aren't exported to CloudWatch Logs.
pendingCloudwatchLogsExports_logTypesToEnable :: Lens' PendingCloudwatchLogsExports (Maybe [Text])

-- | Log types that are in the process of being enabled. After they are
--   enabled, these log types are exported to CloudWatch Logs.
pendingCloudwatchLogsExports_logTypesToDisable :: Lens' PendingCloudwatchLogsExports (Maybe [Text])
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.PendingCloudwatchLogsExports.PendingCloudwatchLogsExports
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.PendingCloudwatchLogsExports.PendingCloudwatchLogsExports
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.PendingCloudwatchLogsExports.PendingCloudwatchLogsExports
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.PendingCloudwatchLogsExports.PendingCloudwatchLogsExports
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.PendingCloudwatchLogsExports.PendingCloudwatchLogsExports
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.PendingCloudwatchLogsExports.PendingCloudwatchLogsExports
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.PendingCloudwatchLogsExports.PendingCloudwatchLogsExports


module Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.PendingMaintenanceAction

-- | Provides information about a pending maintenance action for a
--   resource.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newPendingMaintenanceAction</a> smart constructor.
data PendingMaintenanceAction
PendingMaintenanceAction' :: Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe ISO8601 -> PendingMaintenanceAction

-- | The date of the maintenance window when the action is applied. The
--   maintenance action is applied to the resource during its first
--   maintenance window after this date. If this date is specified, any
--   <tt>next-maintenance</tt> opt-in requests are ignored.
[$sel:autoAppliedAfterDate:PendingMaintenanceAction'] :: PendingMaintenanceAction -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | The type of pending maintenance action that is available for the
--   resource.
[$sel:action:PendingMaintenanceAction'] :: PendingMaintenanceAction -> Maybe Text

-- | Indicates the type of opt-in request that has been received for the
--   resource.
[$sel:optInStatus:PendingMaintenanceAction'] :: PendingMaintenanceAction -> Maybe Text

-- | A description providing more detail about the maintenance action.
[$sel:description:PendingMaintenanceAction'] :: PendingMaintenanceAction -> Maybe Text

-- | The date when the maintenance action is automatically applied. The
--   maintenance action is applied to the resource on this date regardless
--   of the maintenance window for the resource. If this date is specified,
--   any <tt>immediate</tt> opt-in requests are ignored.
[$sel:forcedApplyDate:PendingMaintenanceAction'] :: PendingMaintenanceAction -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | The effective date when the pending maintenance action is applied to
--   the resource. This date takes into account opt-in requests received
--   from the ApplyPendingMaintenanceAction API, the
--   <tt>AutoAppliedAfterDate</tt>, and the <tt>ForcedApplyDate</tt>. This
--   value is blank if an opt-in request has not been received and nothing
--   has been specified as <tt>AutoAppliedAfterDate</tt> or
--   <tt>ForcedApplyDate</tt>.
[$sel:currentApplyDate:PendingMaintenanceAction'] :: PendingMaintenanceAction -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | Create a value of <a>PendingMaintenanceAction</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:autoAppliedAfterDate:PendingMaintenanceAction'</a>,
--   <a>pendingMaintenanceAction_autoAppliedAfterDate</a> - The date of the
--   maintenance window when the action is applied. The maintenance action
--   is applied to the resource during its first maintenance window after
--   this date. If this date is specified, any <tt>next-maintenance</tt>
--   opt-in requests are ignored.
--   
--   <a>$sel:action:PendingMaintenanceAction'</a>,
--   <a>pendingMaintenanceAction_action</a> - The type of pending
--   maintenance action that is available for the resource.
--   
--   <a>$sel:optInStatus:PendingMaintenanceAction'</a>,
--   <a>pendingMaintenanceAction_optInStatus</a> - Indicates the type of
--   opt-in request that has been received for the resource.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:PendingMaintenanceAction'</a>,
--   <a>pendingMaintenanceAction_description</a> - A description providing
--   more detail about the maintenance action.
--   
--   <a>$sel:forcedApplyDate:PendingMaintenanceAction'</a>,
--   <a>pendingMaintenanceAction_forcedApplyDate</a> - The date when the
--   maintenance action is automatically applied. The maintenance action is
--   applied to the resource on this date regardless of the maintenance
--   window for the resource. If this date is specified, any
--   <tt>immediate</tt> opt-in requests are ignored.
--   
--   <a>$sel:currentApplyDate:PendingMaintenanceAction'</a>,
--   <a>pendingMaintenanceAction_currentApplyDate</a> - The effective date
--   when the pending maintenance action is applied to the resource. This
--   date takes into account opt-in requests received from the
--   ApplyPendingMaintenanceAction API, the <tt>AutoAppliedAfterDate</tt>,
--   and the <tt>ForcedApplyDate</tt>. This value is blank if an opt-in
--   request has not been received and nothing has been specified as
--   <tt>AutoAppliedAfterDate</tt> or <tt>ForcedApplyDate</tt>.
newPendingMaintenanceAction :: PendingMaintenanceAction

-- | The date of the maintenance window when the action is applied. The
--   maintenance action is applied to the resource during its first
--   maintenance window after this date. If this date is specified, any
--   <tt>next-maintenance</tt> opt-in requests are ignored.
pendingMaintenanceAction_autoAppliedAfterDate :: Lens' PendingMaintenanceAction (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The type of pending maintenance action that is available for the
--   resource.
pendingMaintenanceAction_action :: Lens' PendingMaintenanceAction (Maybe Text)

-- | Indicates the type of opt-in request that has been received for the
--   resource.
pendingMaintenanceAction_optInStatus :: Lens' PendingMaintenanceAction (Maybe Text)

-- | A description providing more detail about the maintenance action.
pendingMaintenanceAction_description :: Lens' PendingMaintenanceAction (Maybe Text)

-- | The date when the maintenance action is automatically applied. The
--   maintenance action is applied to the resource on this date regardless
--   of the maintenance window for the resource. If this date is specified,
--   any <tt>immediate</tt> opt-in requests are ignored.
pendingMaintenanceAction_forcedApplyDate :: Lens' PendingMaintenanceAction (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The effective date when the pending maintenance action is applied to
--   the resource. This date takes into account opt-in requests received
--   from the ApplyPendingMaintenanceAction API, the
--   <tt>AutoAppliedAfterDate</tt>, and the <tt>ForcedApplyDate</tt>. This
--   value is blank if an opt-in request has not been received and nothing
--   has been specified as <tt>AutoAppliedAfterDate</tt> or
--   <tt>ForcedApplyDate</tt>.
pendingMaintenanceAction_currentApplyDate :: Lens' PendingMaintenanceAction (Maybe UTCTime)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.PendingMaintenanceAction.PendingMaintenanceAction
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.PendingMaintenanceAction.PendingMaintenanceAction
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.PendingMaintenanceAction.PendingMaintenanceAction
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.PendingMaintenanceAction.PendingMaintenanceAction

module Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.PendingModifiedValues

-- | This data type is used as a response element in the ModifyDBInstance
--   action.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newPendingModifiedValues</a> smart constructor.
data PendingModifiedValues
PendingModifiedValues' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe PendingCloudwatchLogsExports -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> PendingModifiedValues

-- | Indicates the database engine version.
[$sel:engineVersion:PendingModifiedValues'] :: PendingModifiedValues -> Maybe Text

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
[$sel:masterUserPassword:PendingModifiedValues'] :: PendingModifiedValues -> Maybe Text

-- | The new DB subnet group for the DB instance.
[$sel:dbSubnetGroupName:PendingModifiedValues'] :: PendingModifiedValues -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the new Provisioned IOPS value for the DB instance that will
--   be applied or is currently being applied.
[$sel:iops:PendingModifiedValues'] :: PendingModifiedValues -> Maybe Int

-- | Contains the new <tt>DBInstanceClass</tt> for the DB instance that
--   will be applied or is currently being applied.
[$sel:dbInstanceClass:PendingModifiedValues'] :: PendingModifiedValues -> Maybe Text

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
[$sel:licenseModel:PendingModifiedValues'] :: PendingModifiedValues -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the identifier of the CA certificate for the DB instance.
[$sel:cACertificateIdentifier:PendingModifiedValues'] :: PendingModifiedValues -> Maybe Text

-- | Contains the new <tt>DBInstanceIdentifier</tt> for the DB instance
--   that will be applied or is currently being applied.
[$sel:dbInstanceIdentifier:PendingModifiedValues'] :: PendingModifiedValues -> Maybe Text

-- | This <tt>PendingCloudwatchLogsExports</tt> structure specifies pending
--   changes to which CloudWatch logs are enabled and which are disabled.
[$sel:pendingCloudwatchLogsExports:PendingModifiedValues'] :: PendingModifiedValues -> Maybe PendingCloudwatchLogsExports

-- | Specifies the pending number of days for which automated backups are
--   retained.
[$sel:backupRetentionPeriod:PendingModifiedValues'] :: PendingModifiedValues -> Maybe Int

-- | Indicates that the Single-AZ DB instance is to change to a Multi-AZ
--   deployment.
[$sel:multiAZ:PendingModifiedValues'] :: PendingModifiedValues -> Maybe Bool

-- | Contains the new <tt>AllocatedStorage</tt> size for the DB instance
--   that will be applied or is currently being applied.
[$sel:allocatedStorage:PendingModifiedValues'] :: PendingModifiedValues -> Maybe Int

-- | Specifies the pending port for the DB instance.
[$sel:port:PendingModifiedValues'] :: PendingModifiedValues -> Maybe Int

-- | Specifies the storage type to be associated with the DB instance.
[$sel:storageType:PendingModifiedValues'] :: PendingModifiedValues -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>PendingModifiedValues</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

module Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Range

-- | A range of integer values.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newRange</a> smart constructor.
data Range
Range' :: Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Range

-- | The maximum value in the range.
[$sel:to:Range'] :: Range -> Maybe Int

-- | The minimum value in the range.
[$sel:from:Range'] :: Range -> Maybe Int

-- | The step value for the range. For example, if you have a range of
--   5,000 to 10,000, with a step value of 1,000, the valid values start at
--   5,000 and step up by 1,000. Even though 7,500 is within the range, it
--   isn't a valid value for the range. The valid values are 5,000, 6,000,
--   7,000, 8,000...
[$sel:step:Range'] :: Range -> Maybe Int

-- | Create a value of <a>Range</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:to:Range'</a>, <a>range_to</a> - The maximum value in the
--   range.
--   
--   <a>$sel:from:Range'</a>, <a>range_from</a> - The minimum value in the
--   range.
--   
--   <a>$sel:step:Range'</a>, <a>range_step</a> - The step value for the
--   range. For example, if you have a range of 5,000 to 10,000, with a
--   step value of 1,000, the valid values start at 5,000 and step up by
--   1,000. Even though 7,500 is within the range, it isn't a valid value
--   for the range. The valid values are 5,000, 6,000, 7,000, 8,000...
newRange :: Range

-- | The maximum value in the range.
range_to :: Lens' Range (Maybe Int)

-- | The minimum value in the range.
range_from :: Lens' Range (Maybe Int)

-- | The step value for the range. For example, if you have a range of
--   5,000 to 10,000, with a step value of 1,000, the valid values start at
--   5,000 and step up by 1,000. Even though 7,500 is within the range, it
--   isn't a valid value for the range. The valid values are 5,000, 6,000,
--   7,000, 8,000...
range_step :: Lens' Range (Maybe Int)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Range.Range
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Range.Range
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Range.Range
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Range.Range
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Range.Range
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Range.Range
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Range.Range

module Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Event

-- | This data type is used as a response element in the DescribeEvents
--   action.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newEvent</a> smart constructor.
data Event
Event' :: Maybe SourceType -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Event

-- | Specifies the source type for this event.
[$sel:sourceType:Event'] :: Event -> Maybe SourceType

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the event.
[$sel:sourceArn:Event'] :: Event -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides the identifier for the source of the event.
[$sel:sourceIdentifier:Event'] :: Event -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the date and time of the event.
[$sel:date:Event'] :: Event -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | Specifies the category for the event.
[$sel:eventCategories:Event'] :: Event -> Maybe [Text]

-- | Provides the text of this event.
[$sel:message:Event'] :: Event -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>Event</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceType:Event'</a>, <a>event_sourceType</a> - Specifies the
--   source type for this event.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceArn:Event'</a>, <a>event_sourceArn</a> - The Amazon
--   Resource Name (ARN) for the event.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceIdentifier:Event'</a>, <a>event_sourceIdentifier</a> -
--   Provides the identifier for the source of the event.
--   
--   <a>$sel:date:Event'</a>, <a>event_date</a> - Specifies the date and
--   time of the event.
--   
--   <a>$sel:eventCategories:Event'</a>, <a>event_eventCategories</a> -
--   Specifies the category for the event.
--   
--   <a>$sel:message:Event'</a>, <a>event_message</a> - Provides the text
--   of this event.
newEvent :: Event

-- | Specifies the source type for this event.
event_sourceType :: Lens' Event (Maybe SourceType)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the event.
event_sourceArn :: Lens' Event (Maybe Text)

-- | Provides the identifier for the source of the event.
event_sourceIdentifier :: Lens' Event (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the date and time of the event.
event_date :: Lens' Event (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | Specifies the category for the event.
event_eventCategories :: Lens' Event (Maybe [Text])

-- | Provides the text of this event.
event_message :: Lens' Event (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Event.Event
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Event.Event
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Event.Event
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Event.Event

module Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Tag

-- | Metadata assigned to an Amazon Neptune resource consisting of a
--   key-value pair.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newTag</a> smart constructor.
data Tag
Tag' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Tag

-- | A value is the optional value of the tag. The string value can be from
--   1 to 256 Unicode characters in length and can't be prefixed with
--   "aws:" or "rds:". The string can only contain only the set of Unicode
--   letters, digits, white-space, '_', '.', '/', '=', '+', '-' (Java
--   regex: "^([\\p{L}\\p{Z}\\p{N}_.:/=+\\-]*)$").
[$sel:value:Tag'] :: Tag -> Maybe Text

-- | A key is the required name of the tag. The string value can be from 1
--   to 128 Unicode characters in length and can't be prefixed with "aws:"
--   or "rds:". The string can only contain only the set of Unicode
--   letters, digits, white-space, '_', '.', '/', '=', '+', '-' (Java
--   regex: "^([\\p{L}\\p{Z}\\p{N}_.:/=+\\-]*)$").
[$sel:key:Tag'] :: Tag -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>Tag</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:value:Tag'</a>, <a>tag_value</a> - A value is the optional
--   value of the tag. The string value can be from 1 to 256 Unicode
--   characters in length and can't be prefixed with "aws:" or "rds:". The
--   string can only contain only the set of Unicode letters, digits,
--   white-space, '_', '.', '/', '=', '+', '-' (Java regex:
--   "^([\\p{L}\\p{Z}\\p{N}_.:/=+\\-]*)$").
--   
--   <a>$sel:key:Tag'</a>, <a>tag_key</a> - A key is the required name of
--   the tag. The string value can be from 1 to 128 Unicode characters in
--   length and can't be prefixed with "aws:" or "rds:". The string can
--   only contain only the set of Unicode letters, digits, white-space,
--   '_', '.', '/', '=', '+', '-' (Java regex:
--   "^([\\p{L}\\p{Z}\\p{N}_.:/=+\\-]*)$").
newTag :: Tag

-- | A value is the optional value of the tag. The string value can be from
--   1 to 256 Unicode characters in length and can't be prefixed with
--   "aws:" or "rds:". The string can only contain only the set of Unicode
--   letters, digits, white-space, '_', '.', '/', '=', '+', '-' (Java
--   regex: "^([\\p{L}\\p{Z}\\p{N}_.:/=+\\-]*)$").
tag_value :: Lens' Tag (Maybe Text)

-- | A key is the required name of the tag. The string value can be from 1
--   to 128 Unicode characters in length and can't be prefixed with "aws:"
--   or "rds:". The string can only contain only the set of Unicode
--   letters, digits, white-space, '_', '.', '/', '=', '+', '-' (Java
--   regex: "^([\\p{L}\\p{Z}\\p{N}_.:/=+\\-]*)$").
tag_key :: Lens' Tag (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Tag.Tag
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Tag.Tag
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Tag.Tag
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Tag.Tag
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.Tag.Tag

--   to.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newUpgradeTarget</a> smart constructor.
data UpgradeTarget

[$sel:engineVersion:UpgradeTarget'] :: UpgradeTarget -> Maybe Text

-- | A value that indicates whether a database engine is upgraded to a
--   major version.
[$sel:isMajorVersionUpgrade:UpgradeTarget'] :: UpgradeTarget -> Maybe Bool

-- | The name of the upgrade target database engine.
[$sel:engine:UpgradeTarget'] :: UpgradeTarget -> Maybe Text

-- | A value that indicates whether the target version is applied to any
--   source DB instances that have AutoMinorVersionUpgrade set to true.
[$sel:autoUpgrade:UpgradeTarget'] :: UpgradeTarget -> Maybe Bool

--   to.

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   target database engine.
--   
--   <a>$sel:isMajorVersionUpgrade:UpgradeTarget'</a>,
--   <a>upgradeTarget_isMajorVersionUpgrade</a> - A value that indicates
--   whether a database engine is upgraded to a major version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:engine:UpgradeTarget'</a>, <a>upgradeTarget_engine</a> - The
--   name of the upgrade target database engine.
--   
--   <a>$sel:autoUpgrade:UpgradeTarget'</a>,
--   <a>upgradeTarget_autoUpgrade</a> - A value that indicates whether the
--   target version is applied to any source DB instances that have
--   AutoMinorVersionUpgrade set to true.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:UpgradeTarget'</a>,
--   <a>upgradeTarget_description</a> - The version of the database engine
--   that a DB instance can be upgraded to.
newUpgradeTarget :: UpgradeTarget

--   major version.

--   source DB instances that have AutoMinorVersionUpgrade set to true.

--   to.
upgradeTarget_description :: Lens' UpgradeTarget (Maybe Text)

module Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.ValidStorageOptions

-- | Information about valid modifications that you can make to your DB
--   instance.
--   
--   Contains the result of a successful call to the
--   DescribeValidDBInstanceModifications action.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newValidStorageOptions</a> smart constructor.
data ValidStorageOptions
ValidStorageOptions' :: Maybe [Range] -> Maybe [Range] -> Maybe [DoubleRange] -> Maybe Text -> ValidStorageOptions

-- | The valid range of storage in gibibytes. For example, 100 to 16384.
[$sel:storageSize:ValidStorageOptions'] :: ValidStorageOptions -> Maybe [Range]

-- | The valid range of provisioned IOPS. For example, 1000-20000.
[$sel:provisionedIops:ValidStorageOptions'] :: ValidStorageOptions -> Maybe [Range]

-- | The valid range of Provisioned IOPS to gibibytes of storage
--   multiplier. For example, 3-10, which means that provisioned IOPS can
--   be between 3 and 10 times storage.
[$sel:iopsToStorageRatio:ValidStorageOptions'] :: ValidStorageOptions -> Maybe [DoubleRange]

-- | The valid storage types for your DB instance. For example, gp2, io1.
[$sel:storageType:ValidStorageOptions'] :: ValidStorageOptions -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ValidStorageOptions</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:storageSize:ValidStorageOptions'</a>,
--   <a>validStorageOptions_storageSize</a> - The valid range of storage in
--   gibibytes. For example, 100 to 16384.
--   
--   <a>$sel:provisionedIops:ValidStorageOptions'</a>,
--   <a>validStorageOptions_provisionedIops</a> - The valid range of
--   provisioned IOPS. For example, 1000-20000.
--   
--   <a>$sel:iopsToStorageRatio:ValidStorageOptions'</a>,
--   <a>validStorageOptions_iopsToStorageRatio</a> - The valid range of
--   Provisioned IOPS to gibibytes of storage multiplier. For example,
--   3-10, which means that provisioned IOPS can be between 3 and 10 times
--   storage.
--   
--   <a>$sel:storageType:ValidStorageOptions'</a>,
--   <a>validStorageOptions_storageType</a> - The valid storage types for
--   your DB instance. For example, gp2, io1.
newValidStorageOptions :: ValidStorageOptions

-- | The valid range of storage in gibibytes. For example, 100 to 16384.
validStorageOptions_storageSize :: Lens' ValidStorageOptions (Maybe [Range])

-- | The valid range of provisioned IOPS. For example, 1000-20000.
validStorageOptions_provisionedIops :: Lens' ValidStorageOptions (Maybe [Range])

-- | The valid range of Provisioned IOPS to gibibytes of storage
--   multiplier. For example, 3-10, which means that provisioned IOPS can
--   be between 3 and 10 times storage.
validStorageOptions_iopsToStorageRatio :: Lens' ValidStorageOptions (Maybe [DoubleRange])

-- | The valid storage types for your DB instance. For example, gp2, io1.
validStorageOptions_storageType :: Lens' ValidStorageOptions (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.ValidStorageOptions.ValidStorageOptions
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.ValidStorageOptions.ValidStorageOptions
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.ValidStorageOptions.ValidStorageOptions
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.ValidStorageOptions.ValidStorageOptions
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.ValidStorageOptions.ValidStorageOptions
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.ValidStorageOptions.ValidStorageOptions
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.ValidStorageOptions.ValidStorageOptions


module Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.ValidDBInstanceModificationsMessage

-- | Information about valid modifications that you can make to your DB
--   instance. Contains the result of a successful call to the
--   DescribeValidDBInstanceModifications action. You can use this
--   information when you call ModifyDBInstance.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newValidDBInstanceModificationsMessage</a> smart
--   constructor.
data ValidDBInstanceModificationsMessage
ValidDBInstanceModificationsMessage' :: Maybe [ValidStorageOptions] -> ValidDBInstanceModificationsMessage

[$sel:storage:ValidDBInstanceModificationsMessage'] :: ValidDBInstanceModificationsMessage -> Maybe [ValidStorageOptions]

-- | Create a value of <a>ValidDBInstanceModificationsMessage</a> with all

--   options for your DB instance.

module Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBInstance

-- | Contains the details of an Amazon Neptune DB instance.
--   
--   This data type is used as a response element in the
--   DescribeDBInstances action.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDBInstance</a> smart constructor.
data DBInstance
DBInstance' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe [DBSecurityGroupMembership] -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [VpcSecurityGroupMembership] -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe DBSubnetGroup -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe [OptionGroupMembership] -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [DBParameterGroupStatus] -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Endpoint -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe PendingModifiedValues -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [DBInstanceStatusInfo] -> Maybe [DomainMembership] -> Maybe Text -> DBInstance

-- | Indicates the database engine version.
[$sel:engineVersion:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides List of DB security group elements containing only
--   <tt>DBSecurityGroup.Name</tt> and <tt>DBSecurityGroup.Status</tt>
--   subelements.
[$sel:dbSecurityGroups:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe [DBSecurityGroupMembership]

-- | Indicates whether or not the DB instance has deletion protection
--   enabled. The instance can't be deleted when deletion protection is
--   enabled. See <a>Deleting a DB Instance</a>.
[$sel:deletionProtection:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Bool

-- | Not supported: The encryption for DB instances is managed by the DB
--   cluster.
[$sel:storageEncrypted:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Bool

-- | If the DB instance is a member of a DB cluster, contains the name of
--   the DB cluster that the DB instance is a member of.
[$sel:dbClusterIdentifier:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | This flag should no longer be used.
[$sel:publiclyAccessible:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Bool

-- | Indicates that minor version patches are applied automatically.
[$sel:autoMinorVersionUpgrade:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Bool

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the DB instance.
[$sel:dbInstanceArn:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
[$sel:masterUsername:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Contains one or more identifiers of the Read Replicas associated with
--   this DB instance.
[$sel:readReplicaDBInstanceIdentifiers:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe [Text]

-- | True if Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM) authentication is
--   enabled, and otherwise false.
[$sel:iAMDatabaseAuthenticationEnabled:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Bool

-- | The ARN for the IAM role that permits Neptune to send Enhanced
--   Monitoring metrics to Amazon CloudWatch Logs.
[$sel:monitoringRoleArn:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the Provisioned IOPS (I/O operations per second) value.
[$sel:iops:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Int

-- | Provides the date and time the DB instance was created.
[$sel:instanceCreateTime:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | Contains the identifier of the source DB instance if this DB instance
--   is a Read Replica.
[$sel:readReplicaSourceDBInstanceIdentifier:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | The interval, in seconds, between points when Enhanced Monitoring
--   metrics are collected for the DB instance.
[$sel:monitoringInterval:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Int

-- | Provides the name of the database engine to be used for this DB
--   instance.
[$sel:engine:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the latest time to which a database can be restored with
--   point-in-time restore.
[$sel:latestRestorableTime:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | Contains the name of the compute and memory capacity class of the DB
--   instance.
[$sel:dbInstanceClass:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | A value that specifies the order in which a Read Replica is promoted
--   to the primary instance after a failure of the existing primary
--   instance.
[$sel:promotionTier:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Int

-- | License model information for this DB instance.
[$sel:licenseModel:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the weekly time range during which system maintenance can
--   occur, in Universal Coordinated Time (UTC).
[$sel:preferredMaintenanceWindow:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | The identifier of the CA certificate for this DB instance.
[$sel:cACertificateIdentifier:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Contains a user-supplied database identifier. This identifier is the
--   unique key that identifies a DB instance.
[$sel:dbInstanceIdentifier:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | <i>(Not supported by Neptune)</i>
[$sel:characterSetName:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Not supported: The encryption for DB instances is managed by the DB
--   cluster.
[$sel:kmsKeyId:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the daily time range during which automated backups are
--   created if automated backups are enabled, as determined by the
--   <tt>BackupRetentionPeriod</tt>.
[$sel:preferredBackupWindow:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the name of the Availability Zone the DB instance is located
--   in.
[$sel:availabilityZone:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides a list of VPC security group elements that the DB instance
--   belongs to.
[$sel:vpcSecurityGroups:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe [VpcSecurityGroupMembership]

-- | Specifies the number of days for which automatic DB snapshots are
--   retained.
[$sel:backupRetentionPeriod:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Int

-- | <i>(Not supported by Neptune)</i>
[$sel:performanceInsightsKMSKeyId:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies information on the subnet group associated with the DB
--   instance, including the name, description, and subnets in the subnet
--   group.
[$sel:dbSubnetGroup:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe DBSubnetGroup

-- | Specifies if the DB instance is a Multi-AZ deployment.
[$sel:multiAZ:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Bool

-- | <i>(Not supported by Neptune)</i>
[$sel:optionGroupMemberships:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe [OptionGroupMembership]

-- | A list of log types that this DB instance is configured to export to
--   CloudWatch Logs.
[$sel:enabledCloudwatchLogsExports:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe [Text]

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Amazon CloudWatch Logs log
--   stream that receives the Enhanced Monitoring metrics data for the DB
--   instance.
[$sel:enhancedMonitoringResourceArn:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | If present, specifies the name of the secondary Availability Zone for
--   a DB instance with multi-AZ support.
[$sel:secondaryAvailabilityZone:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | <i>(Not supported by Neptune)</i>
[$sel:performanceInsightsEnabled:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Bool

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
[$sel:allocatedStorage:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Int

-- | The Amazon Region-unique, immutable identifier for the DB instance.
--   This identifier is found in Amazon CloudTrail log entries whenever the
--   Amazon KMS key for the DB instance is accessed.
[$sel:dbiResourceId:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides the list of DB parameter groups applied to this DB instance.
[$sel:dbParameterGroups:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe [DBParameterGroupStatus]

-- | Specifies whether tags are copied from the DB instance to snapshots of
--   the DB instance.
[$sel:copyTagsToSnapshot:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Bool

-- | Not supported.
[$sel:timezone:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | The ARN from the key store with which the instance is associated for
--   TDE encryption.
[$sel:tdeCredentialArn:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the connection endpoint.
[$sel:endpoint:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Endpoint

-- | Specifies the current state of this database.
[$sel:dbInstanceStatus:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the port that the DB instance listens on. If the DB instance
--   is part of a DB cluster, this can be a different port than the DB
--   cluster port.
[$sel:dbInstancePort:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Int

-- | Specifies that changes to the DB instance are pending. This element is
--   only included when changes are pending. Specific changes are
--   identified by subelements.
[$sel:pendingModifiedValues:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe PendingModifiedValues

-- | Contains one or more identifiers of DB clusters that are Read Replicas
--   of this DB instance.
[$sel:readReplicaDBClusterIdentifiers:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe [Text]

-- | Specifies the storage type associated with DB instance.
[$sel:storageType:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | The status of a Read Replica. If the instance is not a Read Replica,
--   this is blank.
[$sel:statusInfos:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe [DBInstanceStatusInfo]

-- | Not supported
[$sel:domainMemberships:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe [DomainMembership]

-- | The database name.
[$sel:dbName:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>DBInstance</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:engineVersion:DBInstance'</a>, <a>dbInstance_engineVersion</a>
--   - Indicates the database engine version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbSecurityGroups:DBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>dbInstance_dbSecurityGroups</a> - Provides List of DB security
--   group elements containing only <tt>DBSecurityGroup.Name</tt> and
--   <tt>DBSecurityGroup.Status</tt> subelements.
--   
--   <a>$sel:deletionProtection:DBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>dbInstance_deletionProtection</a> - Indicates whether or not the DB
--   instance has deletion protection enabled. The instance can't be

--   Instance</a>.

--   <a>$sel:dbInstanceClass:DBInstance'</a>,

--   Specifies the connection endpoint.

--   <a>$sel:dbInstancePort:DBInstance'</a>,

--   instance listens on. If the DB instance is part of a DB cluster, this
--   can be a different port than the DB cluster port.
--   
--   <a>$sel:pendingModifiedValues:DBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>dbInstance_pendingModifiedValues</a> - Specifies that changes to
--   the DB instance are pending. This element is only included when
--   changes are pending. Specific changes are identified by subelements.

--   <a>$sel:readReplicaDBClusterIdentifiers:DBInstance'</a>,
