--   more identifiers of DB clusters that are Read Replicas of this DB
--   instance.
--   
--   <a>$sel:storageType:DBInstance'</a>, <a>dbInstance_storageType</a> -
--   Specifies the storage type associated with DB instance.
--   
--   <a>$sel:statusInfos:DBInstance'</a>, <a>dbInstance_statusInfos</a> -
--   The status of a Read Replica. If the instance is not a Read Replica,
--   this is blank.
--   
--   <a>$sel:domainMemberships:DBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>dbInstance_domainMemberships</a> - Not supported
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbName:DBInstance'</a>, <a>dbInstance_dbName</a> - The
--   database name.
newDBInstance :: DBInstance

-- | Indicates the database engine version.
dbInstance_engineVersion :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | Provides List of DB security group elements containing only
--   <tt>DBSecurityGroup.Name</tt> and <tt>DBSecurityGroup.Status</tt>
--   subelements.
dbInstance_dbSecurityGroups :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe [DBSecurityGroupMembership])

-- | Indicates whether or not the DB instance has deletion protection
--   enabled. The instance can't be deleted when deletion protection is
--   enabled. See <a>Deleting a DB Instance</a>.
dbInstance_deletionProtection :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Bool)

-- | Not supported: The encryption for DB instances is managed by the DB
--   cluster.
dbInstance_storageEncrypted :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Bool)

-- | If the DB instance is a member of a DB cluster, contains the name of
--   the DB cluster that the DB instance is a member of.
dbInstance_dbClusterIdentifier :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | This flag should no longer be used.
dbInstance_publiclyAccessible :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Bool)

-- | Indicates that minor version patches are applied automatically.
dbInstance_autoMinorVersionUpgrade :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Bool)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the DB instance.
dbInstance_dbInstanceArn :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
dbInstance_masterUsername :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | Contains one or more identifiers of the Read Replicas associated with
--   this DB instance.
dbInstance_readReplicaDBInstanceIdentifiers :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe [Text])

-- | True if Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM) authentication is
--   enabled, and otherwise false.
dbInstance_iAMDatabaseAuthenticationEnabled :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Bool)

-- | The ARN for the IAM role that permits Neptune to send Enhanced
--   Monitoring metrics to Amazon CloudWatch Logs.
dbInstance_monitoringRoleArn :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the Provisioned IOPS (I/O operations per second) value.
dbInstance_iops :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Int)

-- | Provides the date and time the DB instance was created.
dbInstance_instanceCreateTime :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | Contains the identifier of the source DB instance if this DB instance
--   is a Read Replica.
dbInstance_readReplicaSourceDBInstanceIdentifier :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | The interval, in seconds, between points when Enhanced Monitoring
--   metrics are collected for the DB instance.
dbInstance_monitoringInterval :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Int)

-- | Provides the name of the database engine to be used for this DB
--   instance.
dbInstance_engine :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the latest time to which a database can be restored with
--   point-in-time restore.
dbInstance_latestRestorableTime :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | Contains the name of the compute and memory capacity class of the DB
--   instance.
dbInstance_dbInstanceClass :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | A value that specifies the order in which a Read Replica is promoted
--   to the primary instance after a failure of the existing primary
--   instance.
dbInstance_promotionTier :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Int)

-- | License model information for this DB instance.
dbInstance_licenseModel :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the weekly time range during which system maintenance can
--   occur, in Universal Coordinated Time (UTC).
dbInstance_preferredMaintenanceWindow :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | The identifier of the CA certificate for this DB instance.
dbInstance_cACertificateIdentifier :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | Contains a user-supplied database identifier. This identifier is the
--   unique key that identifies a DB instance.
dbInstance_dbInstanceIdentifier :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | <i>(Not supported by Neptune)</i>
dbInstance_characterSetName :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | Not supported: The encryption for DB instances is managed by the DB
--   cluster.
dbInstance_kmsKeyId :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the daily time range during which automated backups are
--   created if automated backups are enabled, as determined by the
--   <tt>BackupRetentionPeriod</tt>.
dbInstance_preferredBackupWindow :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the name of the Availability Zone the DB instance is located
--   in.
dbInstance_availabilityZone :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | Provides a list of VPC security group elements that the DB instance
--   belongs to.
dbInstance_vpcSecurityGroups :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe [VpcSecurityGroupMembership])

-- | Specifies the number of days for which automatic DB snapshots are
--   retained.
dbInstance_backupRetentionPeriod :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Int)

-- | <i>(Not supported by Neptune)</i>
dbInstance_performanceInsightsKMSKeyId :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies information on the subnet group associated with the DB
--   instance, including the name, description, and subnets in the subnet
--   group.
dbInstance_dbSubnetGroup :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe DBSubnetGroup)

-- | Specifies if the DB instance is a Multi-AZ deployment.
dbInstance_multiAZ :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Bool)

-- | <i>(Not supported by Neptune)</i>
dbInstance_optionGroupMemberships :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe [OptionGroupMembership])

-- | A list of log types that this DB instance is configured to export to
--   CloudWatch Logs.
dbInstance_enabledCloudwatchLogsExports :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe [Text])

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Amazon CloudWatch Logs log
--   stream that receives the Enhanced Monitoring metrics data for the DB
--   instance.
dbInstance_enhancedMonitoringResourceArn :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | If present, specifies the name of the secondary Availability Zone for
--   a DB instance with multi-AZ support.
dbInstance_secondaryAvailabilityZone :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | <i>(Not supported by Neptune)</i>
dbInstance_performanceInsightsEnabled :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Bool)

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
dbInstance_allocatedStorage :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Int)

-- | The Amazon Region-unique, immutable identifier for the DB instance.
--   This identifier is found in Amazon CloudTrail log entries whenever the
--   Amazon KMS key for the DB instance is accessed.
dbInstance_dbiResourceId :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | Provides the list of DB parameter groups applied to this DB instance.
dbInstance_dbParameterGroups :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe [DBParameterGroupStatus])

-- | Specifies whether tags are copied from the DB instance to snapshots of
--   the DB instance.
dbInstance_copyTagsToSnapshot :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Bool)

-- | Not supported.
dbInstance_timezone :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | The ARN from the key store with which the instance is associated for
--   TDE encryption.
dbInstance_tdeCredentialArn :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the connection endpoint.
dbInstance_endpoint :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Endpoint)

-- | Specifies the current state of this database.
dbInstance_dbInstanceStatus :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the port that the DB instance listens on. If the DB instance
--   is part of a DB cluster, this can be a different port than the DB
--   cluster port.
dbInstance_dbInstancePort :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Int)

-- | Specifies that changes to the DB instance are pending. This element is
--   only included when changes are pending. Specific changes are
--   identified by subelements.
dbInstance_pendingModifiedValues :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe PendingModifiedValues)

-- | Contains one or more identifiers of DB clusters that are Read Replicas
--   of this DB instance.
dbInstance_readReplicaDBClusterIdentifiers :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe [Text])

-- | Specifies the storage type associated with DB instance.
dbInstance_storageType :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)

-- | The status of a Read Replica. If the instance is not a Read Replica,
--   this is blank.
dbInstance_statusInfos :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe [DBInstanceStatusInfo])

-- | Not supported
dbInstance_domainMemberships :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe [DomainMembership])

-- | The database name.
dbInstance_dbName :: Lens' DBInstance (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBInstance.DBInstance
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBInstance.DBInstance
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBInstance.DBInstance
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBInstance.DBInstance
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBInstance.DBInstance
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBInstance.DBInstance
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBInstance.DBInstance


module Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBCluster

-- | Contains the details of an Amazon Neptune DB cluster.
--   
--   This data type is used as a response element in the DescribeDBClusters
--   action.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDBCluster</a> smart constructor.
data DBCluster
DBCluster' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [DBClusterMember] -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [DBClusterRole] -> Maybe [VpcSecurityGroupMembership] -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe [DBClusterOptionGroupStatus] -> DBCluster

-- | Indicates the database engine version.
[$sel:engineVersion:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the current state of this DB cluster.
[$sel:status:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Indicates whether or not the DB cluster has deletion protection
--   enabled. The database can't be deleted when deletion protection is
--   enabled.
[$sel:deletionProtection:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Bool

-- | Time at which the DB cluster will be automatically restarted.
[$sel:automaticRestartTime:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | Specifies whether the DB cluster is encrypted.
[$sel:storageEncrypted:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Bool

-- | Contains a user-supplied DB cluster identifier. This identifier is the
--   unique key that identifies a DB cluster.
[$sel:dbClusterIdentifier:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides the list of instances that make up the DB cluster.
[$sel:dbClusterMembers:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe [DBClusterMember]

-- | Contains one or more identifiers of the Read Replicas associated with
--   this DB cluster.
[$sel:readReplicaIdentifiers:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe [Text]

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
[$sel:replicationSourceIdentifier:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the ID that Amazon Route 53 assigns when you create a hosted
--   zone.
[$sel:hostedZoneId:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the name of the DB cluster parameter group for the DB
--   cluster.
[$sel:dbClusterParameterGroup:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
[$sel:masterUsername:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | True if mapping of Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM)
--   accounts to database accounts is enabled, and otherwise false.
[$sel:iAMDatabaseAuthenticationEnabled:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Bool

-- | The Amazon Region-unique, immutable identifier for the DB cluster.
--   This identifier is found in Amazon CloudTrail log entries whenever the
--   Amazon KMS key for the DB cluster is accessed.
[$sel:dbClusterResourceId:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the earliest time to which a database can be restored with
--   point-in-time restore.
[$sel:earliestRestorableTime:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | Provides the name of the database engine to be used for this DB
--   cluster.
[$sel:engine:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the DB cluster.
[$sel:dbClusterArn:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Identifies the clone group to which the DB cluster is associated.
[$sel:cloneGroupId:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the latest time to which a database can be restored with
--   point-in-time restore.
[$sel:latestRestorableTime:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | If set to <tt>true</tt>, the DB cluster can be cloned across accounts.
[$sel:crossAccountClone:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specifies the weekly time range during which system maintenance can
--   occur, in Universal Coordinated Time (UTC).
[$sel:preferredMaintenanceWindow:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides the list of EC2 Availability Zones that instances in the DB
--   cluster can be created in.
[$sel:availabilityZones:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe [Text]

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
[$sel:characterSetName:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | If <tt>StorageEncrypted</tt> is true, the Amazon KMS key identifier
--   for the encrypted DB cluster.
[$sel:kmsKeyId:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the daily time range during which automated backups are
--   created if automated backups are enabled, as determined by the
--   <tt>BackupRetentionPeriod</tt>.
[$sel:preferredBackupWindow:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides a list of the Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM)
--   roles that are associated with the DB cluster. IAM roles that are
--   associated with a DB cluster grant permission for the DB cluster to
--   access other Amazon services on your behalf.
[$sel:associatedRoles:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe [DBClusterRole]

-- | Provides a list of VPC security groups that the DB cluster belongs to.
[$sel:vpcSecurityGroups:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe [VpcSecurityGroupMembership]

-- | Specifies the number of days for which automatic DB snapshots are
--   retained.
[$sel:backupRetentionPeriod:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Int

-- | Specifies information on the subnet group associated with the DB
--   cluster, including the name, description, and subnets in the subnet
--   group.
[$sel:dbSubnetGroup:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Contains the name of the initial database of this DB cluster that was
--   provided at create time, if one was specified when the DB cluster was
--   created. This same name is returned for the life of the DB cluster.
[$sel:databaseName:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies whether the DB cluster has instances in multiple
--   Availability Zones.
[$sel:multiAZ:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Bool

-- | A list of log types that this DB cluster is configured to export to
--   CloudWatch Logs.
[$sel:enabledCloudwatchLogsExports:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe [Text]

-- | <tt>AllocatedStorage</tt> always returns 1, because Neptune DB cluster
--   storage size is not fixed, but instead automatically adjusts as
--   needed.
[$sel:allocatedStorage:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Int

-- | /If set to <tt>true</tt>, tags are copied to any snapshot of the DB
--   cluster that is created./
[$sel:copyTagsToSnapshot:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specifies the time when the DB cluster was created, in Universal
--   Coordinated Time (UTC).
[$sel:clusterCreateTime:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | Specifies the connection endpoint for the primary instance of the DB
--   cluster.
[$sel:endpoint:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the progress of the operation as a percentage.
[$sel:percentProgress:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | The reader endpoint for the DB cluster. The reader endpoint for a DB
--   cluster load-balances connections across the Read Replicas that are
--   available in a DB cluster. As clients request new connections to the
--   reader endpoint, Neptune distributes the connection requests among the
--   Read Replicas in the DB cluster. This functionality can help balance
--   your read workload across multiple Read Replicas in your DB cluster.
--   
--   If a failover occurs, and the Read Replica that you are connected to
--   is promoted to be the primary instance, your connection is dropped. To
--   continue sending your read workload to other Read Replicas in the
--   cluster, you can then reconnect to the reader endpoint.
[$sel:readerEndpoint:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the port that the database engine is listening on.
[$sel:port:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Int

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
[$sel:dbClusterOptionGroupMemberships:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe [DBClusterOptionGroupStatus]

--   operation as a percentage.
--

--   Read Replicas in the DB cluster. This functionality can help balance

--   <a>$sel:dbClusterOptionGroupMemberships:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_dbClusterOptionGroupMemberships</a> - Not supported by
--   Neptune.
newDBCluster :: DBCluster

--   point-in-time restore.

dbCluster_cloneGroupId :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

--   point-in-time restore.
dbCluster_latestRestorableTime :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | If set to <tt>true</tt>, the DB cluster can be cloned across accounts.
dbCluster_crossAccountClone :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Bool)

-- | Specifies the weekly time range during which system maintenance can
--   occur, in Universal Coordinated Time (UTC).
dbCluster_preferredMaintenanceWindow :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Provides the list of EC2 Availability Zones that instances in the DB
--   cluster can be created in.
dbCluster_availabilityZones :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe [Text])

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
dbCluster_characterSetName :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | If <tt>StorageEncrypted</tt> is true, the Amazon KMS key identifier
--   for the encrypted DB cluster.
dbCluster_kmsKeyId :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the daily time range during which automated backups are
--   created if automated backups are enabled, as determined by the
--   <tt>BackupRetentionPeriod</tt>.
dbCluster_preferredBackupWindow :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Provides a list of the Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM)
--   roles that are associated with the DB cluster. IAM roles that are
--   associated with a DB cluster grant permission for the DB cluster to
--   access other Amazon services on your behalf.
dbCluster_associatedRoles :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe [DBClusterRole])

-- | Provides a list of VPC security groups that the DB cluster belongs to.
dbCluster_vpcSecurityGroups :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe [VpcSecurityGroupMembership])

-- | Specifies the number of days for which automatic DB snapshots are
--   retained.
dbCluster_backupRetentionPeriod :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Int)

-- | Specifies information on the subnet group associated with the DB
--   cluster, including the name, description, and subnets in the subnet
--   group.
dbCluster_dbSubnetGroup :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Contains the name of the initial database of this DB cluster that was
--   provided at create time, if one was specified when the DB cluster was
--   created. This same name is returned for the life of the DB cluster.
dbCluster_databaseName :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies whether the DB cluster has instances in multiple
--   Availability Zones.
dbCluster_multiAZ :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Bool)

-- | A list of log types that this DB cluster is configured to export to
--   CloudWatch Logs.
dbCluster_enabledCloudwatchLogsExports :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe [Text])

-- | <tt>AllocatedStorage</tt> always returns 1, because Neptune DB cluster
--   storage size is not fixed, but instead automatically adjusts as
--   needed.
dbCluster_allocatedStorage :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Int)

-- | /If set to <tt>true</tt>, tags are copied to any snapshot of the DB
--   cluster that is created./
dbCluster_copyTagsToSnapshot :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Bool)

-- | Specifies the time when the DB cluster was created, in Universal
--   Coordinated Time (UTC).
dbCluster_clusterCreateTime :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | Specifies the connection endpoint for the primary instance of the DB
--   cluster.
dbCluster_endpoint :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the progress of the operation as a percentage.
dbCluster_percentProgress :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | The reader endpoint for the DB cluster. The reader endpoint for a DB
--   cluster load-balances connections across the Read Replicas that are
--   available in a DB cluster. As clients request new connections to the
--   reader endpoint, Neptune distributes the connection requests among the
--   Read Replicas in the DB cluster. This functionality can help balance
--   your read workload across multiple Read Replicas in your DB cluster.
--   
--   If a failover occurs, and the Read Replica that you are connected to
--   is promoted to be the primary instance, your connection is dropped. To
--   continue sending your read workload to other Read Replicas in the
--   cluster, you can then reconnect to the reader endpoint.
dbCluster_readerEndpoint :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the port that the database engine is listening on.
dbCluster_port :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Int)

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
dbCluster_dbClusterOptionGroupMemberships :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe [DBClusterOptionGroupStatus])
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBCluster.DBCluster
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBCluster.DBCluster
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBCluster.DBCluster
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBCluster.DBCluster
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBCluster.DBCluster
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBCluster.DBCluster
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.Neptune.Types.DBCluster.DBCluster

-- | API version <tt>2014-10-31</tt> of the Amazon Neptune SDK
--   configuration.
defaultService :: Service

-- | The DB parameter group is in use or is in an invalid state. If you are
--   attempting to delete the parameter group, you cannot delete it when
--   the parameter group is in this state.
_InvalidDBParameterGroupStateFault :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The source could not be found.
_SourceNotFoundFault :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | <i>CertificateIdentifier</i> does not refer to an existing
--   certificate.

-- | User already has a DB cluster snapshot with the given identifier.
_DBClusterSnapshotAlreadyExistsFault :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | A DB parameter group with the same name exists.
_DBParameterGroupAlreadyExistsFault :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

--   parameter groups.
_DBParameterGroupQuotaExceededFault :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

--   operation.

--   manual DB snapshot with.

-- | The configuration setting for the log types to be enabled for export
--   to CloudWatch Logs for a specific DB instance or DB cluster.
--   
--   The <tt>EnableLogTypes</tt> and <tt>DisableLogTypes</tt> arrays
--   determine which logs will be exported (or not exported) to CloudWatch
--   Logs.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newCloudwatchLogsExportConfiguration</a> smart
--   constructor.
data CloudwatchLogsExportConfiguration

-- | Contains the details of an Amazon Neptune DB cluster.
--   
--   This data type is used as a response element in the DescribeDBClusters
--   action.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDBCluster</a> smart constructor.
data DBCluster
DBCluster' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [DBClusterMember] -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [DBClusterRole] -> Maybe [VpcSecurityGroupMembership] -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe [DBClusterOptionGroupStatus] -> DBCluster

-- | Indicates the database engine version.
[$sel:engineVersion:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the current state of this DB cluster.
[$sel:status:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Indicates whether or not the DB cluster has deletion protection
--   enabled. The database can't be deleted when deletion protection is
--   enabled.
[$sel:deletionProtection:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Bool

-- | Time at which the DB cluster will be automatically restarted.
[$sel:automaticRestartTime:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | Specifies whether the DB cluster is encrypted.
[$sel:storageEncrypted:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Bool

-- | Contains a user-supplied DB cluster identifier. This identifier is the
--   unique key that identifies a DB cluster.
[$sel:dbClusterIdentifier:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides the list of instances that make up the DB cluster.
[$sel:dbClusterMembers:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe [DBClusterMember]

-- | Contains one or more identifiers of the Read Replicas associated with
--   this DB cluster.
[$sel:readReplicaIdentifiers:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe [Text]

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
[$sel:replicationSourceIdentifier:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the ID that Amazon Route 53 assigns when you create a hosted
--   zone.
[$sel:hostedZoneId:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the name of the DB cluster parameter group for the DB
--   cluster.
[$sel:dbClusterParameterGroup:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
[$sel:masterUsername:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | True if mapping of Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM)
--   accounts to database accounts is enabled, and otherwise false.
[$sel:iAMDatabaseAuthenticationEnabled:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Bool

-- | The Amazon Region-unique, immutable identifier for the DB cluster.
--   This identifier is found in Amazon CloudTrail log entries whenever the
--   Amazon KMS key for the DB cluster is accessed.
[$sel:dbClusterResourceId:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the earliest time to which a database can be restored with
--   point-in-time restore.
[$sel:earliestRestorableTime:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | Provides the name of the database engine to be used for this DB
--   cluster.
[$sel:engine:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the DB cluster.
[$sel:dbClusterArn:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Identifies the clone group to which the DB cluster is associated.
[$sel:cloneGroupId:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the latest time to which a database can be restored with
--   point-in-time restore.
[$sel:latestRestorableTime:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | If set to <tt>true</tt>, the DB cluster can be cloned across accounts.
[$sel:crossAccountClone:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specifies the weekly time range during which system maintenance can
--   occur, in Universal Coordinated Time (UTC).
[$sel:preferredMaintenanceWindow:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides the list of EC2 Availability Zones that instances in the DB
--   cluster can be created in.
[$sel:availabilityZones:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe [Text]

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
[$sel:characterSetName:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | If <tt>StorageEncrypted</tt> is true, the Amazon KMS key identifier
--   for the encrypted DB cluster.
[$sel:kmsKeyId:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the daily time range during which automated backups are
--   created if automated backups are enabled, as determined by the
--   <tt>BackupRetentionPeriod</tt>.
[$sel:preferredBackupWindow:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides a list of the Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM)
--   roles that are associated with the DB cluster. IAM roles that are
--   associated with a DB cluster grant permission for the DB cluster to
--   access other Amazon services on your behalf.
[$sel:associatedRoles:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe [DBClusterRole]

-- | Provides a list of VPC security groups that the DB cluster belongs to.
[$sel:vpcSecurityGroups:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe [VpcSecurityGroupMembership]

-- | Specifies the number of days for which automatic DB snapshots are
--   retained.
[$sel:backupRetentionPeriod:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Int

-- | Specifies information on the subnet group associated with the DB
--   cluster, including the name, description, and subnets in the subnet
--   group.
[$sel:dbSubnetGroup:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Contains the name of the initial database of this DB cluster that was
--   provided at create time, if one was specified when the DB cluster was
--   created. This same name is returned for the life of the DB cluster.
[$sel:databaseName:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies whether the DB cluster has instances in multiple
--   Availability Zones.
[$sel:multiAZ:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Bool

-- | A list of log types that this DB cluster is configured to export to
--   CloudWatch Logs.
[$sel:enabledCloudwatchLogsExports:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe [Text]

-- | <tt>AllocatedStorage</tt> always returns 1, because Neptune DB cluster
--   storage size is not fixed, but instead automatically adjusts as
--   needed.
[$sel:allocatedStorage:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Int

-- | /If set to <tt>true</tt>, tags are copied to any snapshot of the DB
--   cluster that is created./
[$sel:copyTagsToSnapshot:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specifies the time when the DB cluster was created, in Universal
--   Coordinated Time (UTC).
[$sel:clusterCreateTime:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | Specifies the connection endpoint for the primary instance of the DB
--   cluster.
[$sel:endpoint:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the progress of the operation as a percentage.
[$sel:percentProgress:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | The reader endpoint for the DB cluster. The reader endpoint for a DB
--   cluster load-balances connections across the Read Replicas that are
--   available in a DB cluster. As clients request new connections to the
--   reader endpoint, Neptune distributes the connection requests among the
--   Read Replicas in the DB cluster. This functionality can help balance
--   your read workload across multiple Read Replicas in your DB cluster.
--   
--   If a failover occurs, and the Read Replica that you are connected to
--   is promoted to be the primary instance, your connection is dropped. To
--   continue sending your read workload to other Read Replicas in the
--   cluster, you can then reconnect to the reader endpoint.
[$sel:readerEndpoint:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the port that the database engine is listening on.
[$sel:port:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe Int

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
[$sel:dbClusterOptionGroupMemberships:DBCluster'] :: DBCluster -> Maybe [DBClusterOptionGroupStatus]

-- | Create a value of <a>DBCluster</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:engineVersion:DBCluster'</a>, <a>dbCluster_engineVersion</a> -
--   Indicates the database engine version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:DBCluster'</a>, <a>dbCluster_status</a> - Specifies the
--   current state of this DB cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:deletionProtection:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_deletionProtection</a> - Indicates whether or not the DB
--   cluster has deletion protection enabled. The database can't be deleted
--   when deletion protection is enabled.
--   
--   <a>$sel:automaticRestartTime:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_automaticRestartTime</a> - Time at which the DB cluster
--   will be automatically restarted.
--   
--   <a>$sel:storageEncrypted:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_storageEncrypted</a> - Specifies whether the DB cluster
--   is encrypted.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbClusterIdentifier:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_dbClusterIdentifier</a> - Contains a user-supplied DB
--   cluster identifier. This identifier is the unique key that identifies
--   a DB cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbClusterMembers:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_dbClusterMembers</a> - Provides the list of instances
--   that make up the DB cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:readReplicaIdentifiers:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_readReplicaIdentifiers</a> - Contains one or more
--   identifiers of the Read Replicas associated with this DB cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:replicationSourceIdentifier:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_replicationSourceIdentifier</a> - Not supported by
--   Neptune.
--   
--   <a>$sel:hostedZoneId:DBCluster'</a>, <a>dbCluster_hostedZoneId</a> -
--   Specifies the ID that Amazon Route 53 assigns when you create a hosted
--   zone.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbClusterParameterGroup:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_dbClusterParameterGroup</a> - Specifies the name of the
--   DB cluster parameter group for the DB cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:masterUsername:DBCluster'</a>, <a>dbCluster_masterUsername</a>
--   - Not supported by Neptune.
--   
--   <a>$sel:iAMDatabaseAuthenticationEnabled:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_iAMDatabaseAuthenticationEnabled</a> - True if mapping of
--   Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM) accounts to database
--   accounts is enabled, and otherwise false.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbClusterResourceId:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_dbClusterResourceId</a> - The Amazon Region-unique,
--   immutable identifier for the DB cluster. This identifier is found in
--   Amazon CloudTrail log entries whenever the Amazon KMS key for the DB
--   cluster is accessed.
--   
--   <a>$sel:earliestRestorableTime:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_earliestRestorableTime</a> - Specifies the earliest time
--   to which a database can be restored with point-in-time restore.
--   
--   <a>$sel:engine:DBCluster'</a>, <a>dbCluster_engine</a> - Provides the
--   name of the database engine to be used for this DB cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbClusterArn:DBCluster'</a>, <a>dbCluster_dbClusterArn</a> -
--   The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the DB cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:cloneGroupId:DBCluster'</a>, <a>dbCluster_cloneGroupId</a> -
--   Identifies the clone group to which the DB cluster is associated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:latestRestorableTime:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_latestRestorableTime</a> - Specifies the latest time to
--   which a database can be restored with point-in-time restore.
--   
--   <a>$sel:crossAccountClone:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_crossAccountClone</a> - If set to <tt>true</tt>, the DB
--   cluster can be cloned across accounts.
--   
--   <a>$sel:preferredMaintenanceWindow:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_preferredMaintenanceWindow</a> - Specifies the weekly
--   time range during which system maintenance can occur, in Universal
--   Coordinated Time (UTC).
--   
--   <a>$sel:availabilityZones:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_availabilityZones</a> - Provides the list of EC2
--   Availability Zones that instances in the DB cluster can be created in.
--   
--   <a>$sel:characterSetName:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_characterSetName</a> - Not supported by Neptune.
--   
--   <a>$sel:kmsKeyId:DBCluster'</a>, <a>dbCluster_kmsKeyId</a> - If
--   <tt>StorageEncrypted</tt> is true, the Amazon KMS key identifier for
--   the encrypted DB cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:preferredBackupWindow:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_preferredBackupWindow</a> - Specifies the daily time
--   range during which automated backups are created if automated backups
--   are enabled, as determined by the <tt>BackupRetentionPeriod</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:associatedRoles:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_associatedRoles</a> - Provides a list of the Amazon
--   Identity and Access Management (IAM) roles that are associated with
--   the DB cluster. IAM roles that are associated with a DB cluster grant
--   permission for the DB cluster to access other Amazon services on your
--   behalf.
--   
--   <a>$sel:vpcSecurityGroups:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_vpcSecurityGroups</a> - Provides a list of VPC security
--   groups that the DB cluster belongs to.
--   
--   <a>$sel:backupRetentionPeriod:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_backupRetentionPeriod</a> - Specifies the number of days
--   for which automatic DB snapshots are retained.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbSubnetGroup:DBCluster'</a>, <a>dbCluster_dbSubnetGroup</a> -
--   Specifies information on the subnet group associated with the DB
--   cluster, including the name, description, and subnets in the subnet
--   group.
--   
--   <a>$sel:databaseName:DBCluster'</a>, <a>dbCluster_databaseName</a> -
--   Contains the name of the initial database of this DB cluster that was
--   provided at create time, if one was specified when the DB cluster was
--   created. This same name is returned for the life of the DB cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:multiAZ:DBCluster'</a>, <a>dbCluster_multiAZ</a> - Specifies
--   whether the DB cluster has instances in multiple Availability Zones.
--   
--   <a>$sel:enabledCloudwatchLogsExports:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_enabledCloudwatchLogsExports</a> - A list of log types
--   that this DB cluster is configured to export to CloudWatch Logs.
--   
--   <a>$sel:allocatedStorage:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_allocatedStorage</a> - <tt>AllocatedStorage</tt> always
--   returns 1, because Neptune DB cluster storage size is not fixed, but
--   instead automatically adjusts as needed.
--   
--   <a>$sel:copyTagsToSnapshot:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_copyTagsToSnapshot</a> - /If set to <tt>true</tt>, tags
--   are copied to any snapshot of the DB cluster that is created./
--   
--   <a>$sel:clusterCreateTime:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_clusterCreateTime</a> - Specifies the time when the DB
--   cluster was created, in Universal Coordinated Time (UTC).
--   
--   <a>$sel:endpoint:DBCluster'</a>, <a>dbCluster_endpoint</a> - Specifies
--   the connection endpoint for the primary instance of the DB cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:percentProgress:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_percentProgress</a> - Specifies the progress of the
--   operation as a percentage.
--   
--   <a>$sel:readerEndpoint:DBCluster'</a>, <a>dbCluster_readerEndpoint</a>
--   - The reader endpoint for the DB cluster. The reader endpoint for a DB
--   cluster load-balances connections across the Read Replicas that are
--   available in a DB cluster. As clients request new connections to the
--   reader endpoint, Neptune distributes the connection requests among the
--   Read Replicas in the DB cluster. This functionality can help balance
--   your read workload across multiple Read Replicas in your DB cluster.
--   
--   If a failover occurs, and the Read Replica that you are connected to
--   is promoted to be the primary instance, your connection is dropped. To
--   continue sending your read workload to other Read Replicas in the
--   cluster, you can then reconnect to the reader endpoint.
--   
--   <a>$sel:port:DBCluster'</a>, <a>dbCluster_port</a> - Specifies the
--   port that the database engine is listening on.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbClusterOptionGroupMemberships:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_dbClusterOptionGroupMemberships</a> - Not supported by
--   Neptune.
newDBCluster :: DBCluster

-- | Indicates the database engine version.
dbCluster_engineVersion :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the current state of this DB cluster.
dbCluster_status :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Indicates whether or not the DB cluster has deletion protection
--   enabled. The database can't be deleted when deletion protection is
--   enabled.
dbCluster_deletionProtection :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Bool)

-- | Time at which the DB cluster will be automatically restarted.
dbCluster_automaticRestartTime :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | Specifies whether the DB cluster is encrypted.
dbCluster_storageEncrypted :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Bool)

-- | Contains a user-supplied DB cluster identifier. This identifier is the
--   unique key that identifies a DB cluster.
dbCluster_dbClusterIdentifier :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Provides the list of instances that make up the DB cluster.
dbCluster_dbClusterMembers :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe [DBClusterMember])

-- | Contains one or more identifiers of the Read Replicas associated with
--   this DB cluster.
dbCluster_readReplicaIdentifiers :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe [Text])

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
dbCluster_replicationSourceIdentifier :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the ID that Amazon Route 53 assigns when you create a hosted
--   zone.
dbCluster_hostedZoneId :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the name of the DB cluster parameter group for the DB
--   cluster.
dbCluster_dbClusterParameterGroup :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
dbCluster_masterUsername :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | True if mapping of Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM)
--   accounts to database accounts is enabled, and otherwise false.
dbCluster_iAMDatabaseAuthenticationEnabled :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Bool)

-- | The Amazon Region-unique, immutable identifier for the DB cluster.
--   This identifier is found in Amazon CloudTrail log entries whenever the
--   Amazon KMS key for the DB cluster is accessed.
dbCluster_dbClusterResourceId :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the earliest time to which a database can be restored with
--   point-in-time restore.
dbCluster_earliestRestorableTime :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | Provides the name of the database engine to be used for this DB
--   cluster.
dbCluster_engine :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the DB cluster.
dbCluster_dbClusterArn :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Identifies the clone group to which the DB cluster is associated.
dbCluster_cloneGroupId :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the latest time to which a database can be restored with
--   point-in-time restore.
dbCluster_latestRestorableTime :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | If set to <tt>true</tt>, the DB cluster can be cloned across accounts.
dbCluster_crossAccountClone :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Bool)

-- | Specifies the weekly time range during which system maintenance can
--   occur, in Universal Coordinated Time (UTC).
dbCluster_preferredMaintenanceWindow :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Provides the list of EC2 Availability Zones that instances in the DB
--   cluster can be created in.
dbCluster_availabilityZones :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe [Text])

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
dbCluster_characterSetName :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | If <tt>StorageEncrypted</tt> is true, the Amazon KMS key identifier
--   for the encrypted DB cluster.
dbCluster_kmsKeyId :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the daily time range during which automated backups are
--   created if automated backups are enabled, as determined by the
--   <tt>BackupRetentionPeriod</tt>.
dbCluster_preferredBackupWindow :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Provides a list of the Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM)
--   roles that are associated with the DB cluster. IAM roles that are
--   associated with a DB cluster grant permission for the DB cluster to
--   access other Amazon services on your behalf.
dbCluster_associatedRoles :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe [DBClusterRole])

-- | Provides a list of VPC security groups that the DB cluster belongs to.
dbCluster_vpcSecurityGroups :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe [VpcSecurityGroupMembership])

-- | Specifies the number of days for which automatic DB snapshots are
--   retained.
dbCluster_backupRetentionPeriod :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Int)

-- | Specifies information on the subnet group associated with the DB
--   cluster, including the name, description, and subnets in the subnet
--   group.
dbCluster_dbSubnetGroup :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Contains the name of the initial database of this DB cluster that was
--   provided at create time, if one was specified when the DB cluster was
--   created. This same name is returned for the life of the DB cluster.
dbCluster_databaseName :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies whether the DB cluster has instances in multiple
--   Availability Zones.
dbCluster_multiAZ :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Bool)

-- | A list of log types that this DB cluster is configured to export to
--   CloudWatch Logs.
dbCluster_enabledCloudwatchLogsExports :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe [Text])

-- | <tt>AllocatedStorage</tt> always returns 1, because Neptune DB cluster
--   storage size is not fixed, but instead automatically adjusts as
--   needed.
dbCluster_allocatedStorage :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Int)

-- | /If set to <tt>true</tt>, tags are copied to any snapshot of the DB
--   cluster that is created./
dbCluster_copyTagsToSnapshot :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Bool)

-- | Specifies the time when the DB cluster was created, in Universal
--   Coordinated Time (UTC).
dbCluster_clusterCreateTime :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | Specifies the connection endpoint for the primary instance of the DB
--   cluster.
dbCluster_endpoint :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the progress of the operation as a percentage.
dbCluster_percentProgress :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | The reader endpoint for the DB cluster. The reader endpoint for a DB
--   cluster load-balances connections across the Read Replicas that are
--   available in a DB cluster. As clients request new connections to the
--   reader endpoint, Neptune distributes the connection requests among the
--   Read Replicas in the DB cluster. This functionality can help balance
--   your read workload across multiple Read Replicas in your DB cluster.
--   
--   If a failover occurs, and the Read Replica that you are connected to
--   is promoted to be the primary instance, your connection is dropped. To
--   continue sending your read workload to other Read Replicas in the
--   cluster, you can then reconnect to the reader endpoint.
dbCluster_readerEndpoint :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the port that the database engine is listening on.
dbCluster_port :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe Int)

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
dbCluster_dbClusterOptionGroupMemberships :: Lens' DBCluster (Maybe [DBClusterOptionGroupStatus])

-- | This data type represents the information you need to connect to an
--   Amazon Neptune DB cluster. This data type is used as a response
--   element in the following actions:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>CreateDBClusterEndpoint</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>DescribeDBClusterEndpoints</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>ModifyDBClusterEndpoint</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>DeleteDBClusterEndpoint</pre></li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   For the data structure that represents Amazon Neptune DB instance
--   endpoints, see <tt>Endpoint</tt>.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDBClusterEndpoint</a> smart constructor.
data DBClusterEndpoint
DBClusterEndpoint' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> DBClusterEndpoint

-- | The current status of the endpoint. One of: <tt>creating</tt>,
--   <tt>available</tt>, <tt>deleting</tt>, <tt>inactive</tt>,
--   <tt>modifying</tt>. The <tt>inactive</tt> state applies to an endpoint
--   that cannot be used for a certain kind of cluster, such as a
--   <tt>writer</tt> endpoint for a read-only secondary cluster in a global
--   database.
[$sel:status:DBClusterEndpoint'] :: DBClusterEndpoint -> Maybe Text

-- | The DB cluster identifier of the DB cluster associated with the
--   endpoint. This parameter is stored as a lowercase string.
[$sel:dbClusterIdentifier:DBClusterEndpoint'] :: DBClusterEndpoint -> Maybe Text

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the endpoint.
[$sel:dbClusterEndpointArn:DBClusterEndpoint'] :: DBClusterEndpoint -> Maybe Text

-- | The type associated with a custom endpoint. One of: <tt>READER</tt>,
--   <tt>WRITER</tt>, <tt>ANY</tt>.
[$sel:customEndpointType:DBClusterEndpoint'] :: DBClusterEndpoint -> Maybe Text

-- | List of DB instance identifiers that are part of the custom endpoint
--   group.
[$sel:staticMembers:DBClusterEndpoint'] :: DBClusterEndpoint -> Maybe [Text]

-- | The type of the endpoint. One of: <tt>READER</tt>, <tt>WRITER</tt>,
--   <tt>CUSTOM</tt>.
[$sel:endpointType:DBClusterEndpoint'] :: DBClusterEndpoint -> Maybe Text

-- | The identifier associated with the endpoint. This parameter is stored
--   as a lowercase string.
[$sel:dbClusterEndpointIdentifier:DBClusterEndpoint'] :: DBClusterEndpoint -> Maybe Text

-- | The DNS address of the endpoint.
[$sel:endpoint:DBClusterEndpoint'] :: DBClusterEndpoint -> Maybe Text

-- | A unique system-generated identifier for an endpoint. It remains the
--   same for the whole life of the endpoint.
[$sel:dbClusterEndpointResourceIdentifier:DBClusterEndpoint'] :: DBClusterEndpoint -> Maybe Text

-- | List of DB instance identifiers that aren't part of the custom
--   endpoint group. All other eligible instances are reachable through the
--   custom endpoint. Only relevant if the list of static members is empty.
[$sel:excludedMembers:DBClusterEndpoint'] :: DBClusterEndpoint -> Maybe [Text]

--   
--   <a>$sel:dbClusterIdentifier:DBClusterEndpoint'</a>,

--

--   <a>dbClusterEndpoint_staticMembers</a> - List of DB instance
--   identifiers that are part of the custom endpoint group.
--   
--   <a>$sel:endpointType:DBClusterEndpoint'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterEndpoint_endpointType</a> - The type of the endpoint. One
--   of: <tt>READER</tt>, <tt>WRITER</tt>, <tt>CUSTOM</tt>.

--   eligible instances are reachable through the custom endpoint. Only
--   relevant if the list of static members is empty.

-- | Contains information about an instance that is part of a DB cluster.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDBClusterMember</a> smart constructor.
data DBClusterMember
DBClusterMember' :: Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> DBClusterMember

-- | A value that specifies the order in which a Read Replica is promoted
--   to the primary instance after a failure of the existing primary
--   instance.
[$sel:promotionTier:DBClusterMember'] :: DBClusterMember -> Maybe Int

-- | Specifies the instance identifier for this member of the DB cluster.
[$sel:dbInstanceIdentifier:DBClusterMember'] :: DBClusterMember -> Maybe Text

-- | Value that is <tt>true</tt> if the cluster member is the primary
--   instance for the DB cluster and <tt>false</tt> otherwise.
[$sel:isClusterWriter:DBClusterMember'] :: DBClusterMember -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specifies the status of the DB cluster parameter group for this member
--   of the DB cluster.
[$sel:dbClusterParameterGroupStatus:DBClusterMember'] :: DBClusterMember -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>DBClusterMember</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:promotionTier:DBClusterMember'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterMember_promotionTier</a> - A value that specifies the
--   order in which a Read Replica is promoted to the primary instance
--   after a failure of the existing primary instance.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbInstanceIdentifier:DBClusterMember'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterMember_dbInstanceIdentifier</a> - Specifies the instance
--   identifier for this member of the DB cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:isClusterWriter:DBClusterMember'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterMember_isClusterWriter</a> - Value that is <tt>true</tt>
--   if the cluster member is the primary instance for the DB cluster and
--   <tt>false</tt> otherwise.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbClusterParameterGroupStatus:DBClusterMember'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterMember_dbClusterParameterGroupStatus</a> - Specifies the
--   status of the DB cluster parameter group for this member of the DB
--   cluster.
newDBClusterMember :: DBClusterMember

--   to the primary instance after a failure of the existing primary
--   instance.
dbClusterMember_promotionTier :: Lens' DBClusterMember (Maybe Int)

dbClusterMember_dbInstanceIdentifier :: Lens' DBClusterMember (Maybe Text)

--   instance for the DB cluster and <tt>false</tt> otherwise.

--   of the DB cluster.

-- | Describes an Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM) role that is
--   associated with a DB cluster.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDBClusterRole</a> smart constructor.
data DBClusterRole
DBClusterRole' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> DBClusterRole

-- | Describes the state of association between the IAM role and the DB
--   cluster. The Status property returns one of the following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>ACTIVE</tt> - the IAM role ARN is associated with the DB
--   cluster and can be used to access other Amazon services on your
--   behalf.</li>
--   <li><tt>PENDING</tt> - the IAM role ARN is being associated with the
--   DB cluster.</li>
--   <li><tt>INVALID</tt> - the IAM role ARN is associated with the DB
--   cluster, but the DB cluster is unable to assume the IAM role in order
--   to access other Amazon services on your behalf.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:status:DBClusterRole'] :: DBClusterRole -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the feature associated with the Amazon Identity and Access
--   Management (IAM) role. For the list of supported feature names, see
--   DBEngineVersion.
[$sel:featureName:DBClusterRole'] :: DBClusterRole -> Maybe Text

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the IAM role that is associated with
--   the DB cluster.
[$sel:roleArn:DBClusterRole'] :: DBClusterRole -> Maybe Text

-- | Contains the details for an Amazon Neptune DB cluster snapshot
--   
--   This data type is used as a response element in the
--   DescribeDBClusterSnapshots action.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDBClusterSnapshot</a> smart constructor.
data DBClusterSnapshot
DBClusterSnapshot' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> DBClusterSnapshot

-- | Provides the version of the database engine for this DB cluster
--   snapshot.
[$sel:engineVersion:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the status of this DB cluster snapshot.
[$sel:status:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies whether the DB cluster snapshot is encrypted.
[$sel:storageEncrypted:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specifies the DB cluster identifier of the DB cluster that this DB
--   cluster snapshot was created from.
[$sel:dbClusterIdentifier:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
[$sel:masterUsername:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | True if mapping of Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM)
--   accounts to database accounts is enabled, and otherwise false.
[$sel:iAMDatabaseAuthenticationEnabled:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Bool

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the DB cluster snapshot.
[$sel:dbClusterSnapshotArn:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides the VPC ID associated with the DB cluster snapshot.
[$sel:vpcId:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the identifier for a DB cluster snapshot. Must match the
--   identifier of an existing snapshot.
--   
--   After you restore a DB cluster using a
--   <tt>DBClusterSnapshotIdentifier</tt>, you must specify the same
--   <tt>DBClusterSnapshotIdentifier</tt> for any future updates to the DB
--   cluster. When you specify this property for an update, the DB cluster
--   is not restored from the snapshot again, and the data in the database
--   is not changed.
--   
--   However, if you don't specify the
--   <tt>DBClusterSnapshotIdentifier</tt>, an empty DB cluster is created,
--   and the original DB cluster is deleted. If you specify a property that
--   is different from the previous snapshot restore property, the DB
--   cluster is restored from the snapshot specified by the
--   <tt>DBClusterSnapshotIdentifier</tt>, and the original DB cluster is
--   deleted.
[$sel:dbClusterSnapshotIdentifier:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the name of the database engine.
[$sel:engine:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides the license model information for this DB cluster snapshot.
[$sel:licenseModel:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides the list of EC2 Availability Zones that instances in the DB
--   cluster snapshot can be restored in.
[$sel:availabilityZones:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe [Text]

-- | Provides the type of the DB cluster snapshot.
[$sel:snapshotType:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | If <tt>StorageEncrypted</tt> is true, the Amazon KMS key identifier
--   for the encrypted DB cluster snapshot.
[$sel:kmsKeyId:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides the time when the snapshot was taken, in Universal
--   Coordinated Time (UTC).
[$sel:snapshotCreateTime:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | Specifies the allocated storage size in gibibytes (GiB).
[$sel:allocatedStorage:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Int

-- | If the DB cluster snapshot was copied from a source DB cluster
--   snapshot, the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the source DB cluster
--   snapshot, otherwise, a null value.
[$sel:sourceDBClusterSnapshotArn:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the time when the DB cluster was created, in Universal
--   Coordinated Time (UTC).
[$sel:clusterCreateTime:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | Specifies the percentage of the estimated data that has been
--   transferred.
[$sel:percentProgress:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Int

-- | Specifies the port that the DB cluster was listening on at the time of
--   the snapshot.
[$sel:port:DBClusterSnapshot'] :: DBClusterSnapshot -> Maybe Int

-- | Contains the name and values of a manual DB cluster snapshot
--   attribute.

--   Amazon accounts to restore a manual DB cluster snapshot. For more
--   information, see the ModifyDBClusterSnapshotAttribute API action.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDBClusterSnapshotAttribute</a> smart constructor.

DBClusterSnapshotAttribute' :: Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> DBClusterSnapshotAttribute

--

--   this element returns a list of IDs of the Amazon accounts that are
--   authorized to copy or restore the manual DB cluster snapshot. If a
--   value of <tt>all</tt> is in the list, then the manual DB cluster
--   snapshot is public and available for any Amazon account to copy or
--   restore.
[$sel:attributeValues:DBClusterSnapshotAttribute'] :: DBClusterSnapshotAttribute -> Maybe [Text]

--   ModifyDBClusterSnapshotAttribute API action.
[$sel:attributeName:DBClusterSnapshotAttribute'] :: DBClusterSnapshotAttribute -> Maybe Text

-- | This data type is used as a response element in the action
--   DescribeDBEngineVersions.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDBEngineVersion</a> smart constructor.
data DBEngineVersion
DBEngineVersion' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe CharacterSet -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [CharacterSet] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [UpgradeTarget] -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe [Timezone] -> Maybe [Text] -> DBEngineVersion

-- | The version number of the database engine.
[$sel:engineVersion:DBEngineVersion'] :: DBEngineVersion -> Maybe Text

-- | The description of the database engine version.
[$sel:dbEngineVersionDescription:DBEngineVersion'] :: DBEngineVersion -> Maybe Text

-- | <i>(Not supported by Neptune)</i>
[$sel:defaultCharacterSet:DBEngineVersion'] :: DBEngineVersion -> Maybe CharacterSet

-- | The name of the database engine.
[$sel:engine:DBEngineVersion'] :: DBEngineVersion -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the DB parameter group family for the database engine.
[$sel:dbParameterGroupFamily:DBEngineVersion'] :: DBEngineVersion -> Maybe Text

-- | <i>(Not supported by Neptune)</i>
[$sel:supportedCharacterSets:DBEngineVersion'] :: DBEngineVersion -> Maybe [CharacterSet]

-- | The description of the database engine.
[$sel:dbEngineDescription:DBEngineVersion'] :: DBEngineVersion -> Maybe Text

-- | A list of engine versions that this database engine version can be
--   upgraded to.
[$sel:validUpgradeTarget:DBEngineVersion'] :: DBEngineVersion -> Maybe [UpgradeTarget]

-- | A value that indicates whether the engine version supports exporting
--   the log types specified by ExportableLogTypes to CloudWatch Logs.
[$sel:supportsLogExportsToCloudwatchLogs:DBEngineVersion'] :: DBEngineVersion -> Maybe Bool

-- | Indicates whether the database engine version supports read replicas.
[$sel:supportsReadReplica:DBEngineVersion'] :: DBEngineVersion -> Maybe Bool

-- | A list of the time zones supported by this engine for the
--   <tt>Timezone</tt> parameter of the <tt>CreateDBInstance</tt> action.
[$sel:supportedTimezones:DBEngineVersion'] :: DBEngineVersion -> Maybe [Timezone]

-- | The types of logs that the database engine has available for export to
--   CloudWatch Logs.
[$sel:exportableLogTypes:DBEngineVersion'] :: DBEngineVersion -> Maybe [Text]

-- | Create a value of <a>DBEngineVersion</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:engineVersion:DBEngineVersion'</a>,
--   <a>dbEngineVersion_engineVersion</a> - The version number of the
--   database engine.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbEngineVersionDescription:DBEngineVersion'</a>,
--   <a>dbEngineVersion_dbEngineVersionDescription</a> - The description of
--   the database engine version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:defaultCharacterSet:DBEngineVersion'</a>,
--   <a>dbEngineVersion_defaultCharacterSet</a> - <i>(Not supported by
--   Neptune)</i>
--   
--   <a>$sel:engine:DBEngineVersion'</a>, <a>dbEngineVersion_engine</a> -
--   The name of the database engine.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbParameterGroupFamily:DBEngineVersion'</a>,
--   <a>dbEngineVersion_dbParameterGroupFamily</a> - The name of the DB
--   parameter group family for the database engine.
--   
--   <a>$sel:supportedCharacterSets:DBEngineVersion'</a>,
--   <a>dbEngineVersion_supportedCharacterSets</a> - <i>(Not supported by
--   Neptune)</i>
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbEngineDescription:DBEngineVersion'</a>,
--   <a>dbEngineVersion_dbEngineDescription</a> - The description of the
--   database engine.
--   
--   <a>$sel:validUpgradeTarget:DBEngineVersion'</a>,
--   <a>dbEngineVersion_validUpgradeTarget</a> - A list of engine versions
--   that this database engine version can be upgraded to.
--   
--   <a>$sel:supportsLogExportsToCloudwatchLogs:DBEngineVersion'</a>,
--   <a>dbEngineVersion_supportsLogExportsToCloudwatchLogs</a> - A value
--   that indicates whether the engine version supports exporting the log
--   types specified by ExportableLogTypes to CloudWatch Logs.
--   
--   <a>$sel:supportsReadReplica:DBEngineVersion'</a>,
--   <a>dbEngineVersion_supportsReadReplica</a> - Indicates whether the
--   database engine version supports read replicas.
--   
--   <a>$sel:supportedTimezones:DBEngineVersion'</a>,
--   <a>dbEngineVersion_supportedTimezones</a> - A list of the time zones
--   supported by this engine for the <tt>Timezone</tt> parameter of the
--   <tt>CreateDBInstance</tt> action.
--   
--   <a>$sel:exportableLogTypes:DBEngineVersion'</a>,
--   <a>dbEngineVersion_exportableLogTypes</a> - The types of logs that the
--   database engine has available for export to CloudWatch Logs.
newDBEngineVersion :: DBEngineVersion

-- | The version number of the database engine.
dbEngineVersion_engineVersion :: Lens' DBEngineVersion (Maybe Text)

-- | The description of the database engine version.
dbEngineVersion_dbEngineVersionDescription :: Lens' DBEngineVersion (Maybe Text)

-- | <i>(Not supported by Neptune)</i>
dbEngineVersion_defaultCharacterSet :: Lens' DBEngineVersion (Maybe CharacterSet)

-- | The name of the database engine.
dbEngineVersion_engine :: Lens' DBEngineVersion (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of the DB parameter group family for the database engine.
dbEngineVersion_dbParameterGroupFamily :: Lens' DBEngineVersion (Maybe Text)

-- | <i>(Not supported by Neptune)</i>
dbEngineVersion_supportedCharacterSets :: Lens' DBEngineVersion (Maybe [CharacterSet])

-- | The description of the database engine.
dbEngineVersion_dbEngineDescription :: Lens' DBEngineVersion (Maybe Text)

-- | A list of engine versions that this database engine version can be
--   upgraded to.
dbEngineVersion_validUpgradeTarget :: Lens' DBEngineVersion (Maybe [UpgradeTarget])

-- | A value that indicates whether the engine version supports exporting
--   the log types specified by ExportableLogTypes to CloudWatch Logs.
dbEngineVersion_supportsLogExportsToCloudwatchLogs :: Lens' DBEngineVersion (Maybe Bool)

-- | Indicates whether the database engine version supports read replicas.
dbEngineVersion_supportsReadReplica :: Lens' DBEngineVersion (Maybe Bool)

--   <tt>Timezone</tt> parameter of the <tt>CreateDBInstance</tt> action.
dbEngineVersion_supportedTimezones :: Lens' DBEngineVersion (Maybe [Timezone])

-- | The types of logs that the database engine has available for export to
--   CloudWatch Logs.
dbEngineVersion_exportableLogTypes :: Lens' DBEngineVersion (Maybe [Text])

-- | Contains the details of an Amazon Neptune DB instance.
--   
--   This data type is used as a response element in the
--   DescribeDBInstances action.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDBInstance</a> smart constructor.
data DBInstance
DBInstance' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe [DBSecurityGroupMembership] -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [VpcSecurityGroupMembership] -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe DBSubnetGroup -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe [OptionGroupMembership] -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [DBParameterGroupStatus] -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Endpoint -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe PendingModifiedValues -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [DBInstanceStatusInfo] -> Maybe [DomainMembership] -> Maybe Text -> DBInstance

-- | Indicates the database engine version.
[$sel:engineVersion:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides List of DB security group elements containing only
--   <tt>DBSecurityGroup.Name</tt> and <tt>DBSecurityGroup.Status</tt>
--   subelements.
[$sel:dbSecurityGroups:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe [DBSecurityGroupMembership]

-- | Indicates whether or not the DB instance has deletion protection
--   enabled. The instance can't be deleted when deletion protection is
--   enabled. See <a>Deleting a DB Instance</a>.
[$sel:deletionProtection:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Bool

-- | Not supported: The encryption for DB instances is managed by the DB
--   cluster.
[$sel:storageEncrypted:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Bool

-- | If the DB instance is a member of a DB cluster, contains the name of
--   the DB cluster that the DB instance is a member of.
[$sel:dbClusterIdentifier:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | This flag should no longer be used.
[$sel:publiclyAccessible:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Bool

-- | Indicates that minor version patches are applied automatically.
[$sel:autoMinorVersionUpgrade:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Bool

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the DB instance.
[$sel:dbInstanceArn:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
[$sel:masterUsername:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Contains one or more identifiers of the Read Replicas associated with
--   this DB instance.
[$sel:readReplicaDBInstanceIdentifiers:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe [Text]

-- | True if Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM) authentication is
--   enabled, and otherwise false.
[$sel:iAMDatabaseAuthenticationEnabled:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Bool

-- | The ARN for the IAM role that permits Neptune to send Enhanced
--   Monitoring metrics to Amazon CloudWatch Logs.
[$sel:monitoringRoleArn:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the Provisioned IOPS (I/O operations per second) value.
[$sel:iops:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Int

-- | Provides the date and time the DB instance was created.
[$sel:instanceCreateTime:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | Contains the identifier of the source DB instance if this DB instance
--   is a Read Replica.
[$sel:readReplicaSourceDBInstanceIdentifier:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | The interval, in seconds, between points when Enhanced Monitoring
--   metrics are collected for the DB instance.
[$sel:monitoringInterval:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Int

-- | Provides the name of the database engine to be used for this DB
--   instance.
[$sel:engine:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the latest time to which a database can be restored with
--   point-in-time restore.
[$sel:latestRestorableTime:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe ISO8601

-- | Contains the name of the compute and memory capacity class of the DB
--   instance.
[$sel:dbInstanceClass:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | A value that specifies the order in which a Read Replica is promoted
--   to the primary instance after a failure of the existing primary
--   instance.
[$sel:promotionTier:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Int

-- | License model information for this DB instance.
[$sel:licenseModel:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the weekly time range during which system maintenance can
--   occur, in Universal Coordinated Time (UTC).
[$sel:preferredMaintenanceWindow:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | The identifier of the CA certificate for this DB instance.
[$sel:cACertificateIdentifier:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Contains a user-supplied database identifier. This identifier is the
--   unique key that identifies a DB instance.
[$sel:dbInstanceIdentifier:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | <i>(Not supported by Neptune)</i>
[$sel:characterSetName:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Not supported: The encryption for DB instances is managed by the DB
--   cluster.
[$sel:kmsKeyId:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the daily time range during which automated backups are
--   created if automated backups are enabled, as determined by the
--   <tt>BackupRetentionPeriod</tt>.
[$sel:preferredBackupWindow:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the name of the Availability Zone the DB instance is located
--   in.
[$sel:availabilityZone:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides a list of VPC security group elements that the DB instance
--   belongs to.
[$sel:vpcSecurityGroups:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe [VpcSecurityGroupMembership]

-- | Specifies the number of days for which automatic DB snapshots are
--   retained.
[$sel:backupRetentionPeriod:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Int

-- | <i>(Not supported by Neptune)</i>
[$sel:performanceInsightsKMSKeyId:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies information on the subnet group associated with the DB
--   instance, including the name, description, and subnets in the subnet
--   group.
[$sel:dbSubnetGroup:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe DBSubnetGroup

-- | Specifies if the DB instance is a Multi-AZ deployment.
[$sel:multiAZ:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Bool

-- | <i>(Not supported by Neptune)</i>
[$sel:optionGroupMemberships:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe [OptionGroupMembership]

-- | A list of log types that this DB instance is configured to export to
--   CloudWatch Logs.
[$sel:enabledCloudwatchLogsExports:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe [Text]

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Amazon CloudWatch Logs log
--   stream that receives the Enhanced Monitoring metrics data for the DB
--   instance.
[$sel:enhancedMonitoringResourceArn:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | If present, specifies the name of the secondary Availability Zone for
--   a DB instance with multi-AZ support.
[$sel:secondaryAvailabilityZone:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | <i>(Not supported by Neptune)</i>
[$sel:performanceInsightsEnabled:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Bool

-- | Not supported by Neptune.
[$sel:allocatedStorage:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Int

-- | The Amazon Region-unique, immutable identifier for the DB instance.
--   This identifier is found in Amazon CloudTrail log entries whenever the
--   Amazon KMS key for the DB instance is accessed.
[$sel:dbiResourceId:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Provides the list of DB parameter groups applied to this DB instance.
[$sel:dbParameterGroups:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe [DBParameterGroupStatus]

-- | Specifies whether tags are copied from the DB instance to snapshots of
--   the DB instance.
[$sel:copyTagsToSnapshot:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Bool

-- | Not supported.
[$sel:timezone:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | The ARN from the key store with which the instance is associated for
--   TDE encryption.
[$sel:tdeCredentialArn:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the connection endpoint.
[$sel:endpoint:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Endpoint

-- | Specifies the current state of this database.
[$sel:dbInstanceStatus:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the port that the DB instance listens on. If the DB instance
--   is part of a DB cluster, this can be a different port than the DB
--   cluster port.
[$sel:dbInstancePort:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Int

-- | Specifies that changes to the DB instance are pending. This element is
--   only included when changes are pending. Specific changes are
--   identified by subelements.
[$sel:pendingModifiedValues:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe PendingModifiedValues

-- | Contains one or more identifiers of DB clusters that are Read Replicas
--   of this DB instance.
[$sel:readReplicaDBClusterIdentifiers:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe [Text]

-- | Specifies the storage type associated with DB instance.
[$sel:storageType:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | The status of a Read Replica. If the instance is not a Read Replica,
--   this is blank.
[$sel:statusInfos:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe [DBInstanceStatusInfo]

-- | Not supported
[$sel:domainMemberships:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe [DomainMembership]

-- | The database name.
[$sel:dbName:DBInstance'] :: DBInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>DBInstance</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
