--   between points when Enhanced Monitoring metrics are collected for the
--   DB instance. To disable collecting Enhanced Monitoring metrics,
--   specify 0. The default is 0.
--   
--   If <tt>MonitoringRoleArn</tt> is specified, then you must also set
--   <tt>MonitoringInterval</tt> to a value other than 0.
--   
--   Valid Values: <tt>0, 1, 5, 10, 15, 30, 60</tt>
--   
--   <a>$sel:tdeCredentialPassword:CreateDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>createDBInstance_tdeCredentialPassword</a> - The password for the
--   given ARN from the key store in order to access the device.
--   
--   <a>$sel:promotionTier:CreateDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>createDBInstance_promotionTier</a> - A value that specifies the
--   order in which an Read Replica is promoted to the primary instance
--   after a failure of the existing primary instance.
--   
--   Default: 1
--   
--   Valid Values: 0 - 15
--   
--   <a>$sel:licenseModel:CreateDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>createDBInstance_licenseModel</a> - License model information for
--   this DB instance.
--   
--   Valid values: <tt>license-included</tt> |
--   <tt>bring-your-own-license</tt> | <tt>general-public-license</tt>
--   
--   <a>$sel:preferredMaintenanceWindow:CreateDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>createDBInstance_preferredMaintenanceWindow</a> - The time range
--   each week during which system maintenance can occur, in Universal
--   Coordinated Time (UTC).
--   
--   Format: <tt>ddd:hh24:mi-ddd:hh24:mi</tt>
--   
--   The default is a 30-minute window selected at random from an 8-hour
--   block of time for each Amazon Region, occurring on a random day of the
--   week.
--   
--   Valid Days: Mon, Tue, Wed, Thu, Fri, Sat, Sun.
--   
--   Constraints: Minimum 30-minute window.
--   
--   <a>$sel:characterSetName:CreateDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>createDBInstance_characterSetName</a> - <i>(Not supported by
--   Neptune)</i>
--   
--   <a>$sel:enablePerformanceInsights:CreateDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>createDBInstance_enablePerformanceInsights</a> - <i>(Not supported
--   by Neptune)</i>
--   
--   <a>$sel:kmsKeyId:CreateDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>createDBInstance_kmsKeyId</a> - The Amazon KMS key identifier for
--   an encrypted DB instance.
--   
--   The KMS key identifier is the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the KMS
--   encryption key. If you are creating a DB instance with the same Amazon
--   account that owns the KMS encryption key used to encrypt the new DB
--   instance, then you can use the KMS key alias instead of the ARN for
--   the KM encryption key.
--   
--   Not applicable. The KMS key identifier is managed by the DB cluster.
--   For more information, see CreateDBCluster.
--   
--   If the <tt>StorageEncrypted</tt> parameter is true, and you do not
--   specify a value for the <tt>KmsKeyId</tt> parameter, then Amazon
--   Neptune will use your default encryption key. Amazon KMS creates the
--   default encryption key for your Amazon account. Your Amazon account
--   has a different default encryption key for each Amazon Region.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbParameterGroupName:CreateDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>createDBInstance_dbParameterGroupName</a> - The name of the DB
--   parameter group to associate with this DB instance. If this argument
--   is omitted, the default DBParameterGroup for the specified engine is
--   used.
--   
--   Constraints:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Must be 1 to 255 letters, numbers, or hyphens.</li>
--   <li>First character must be a letter</li>
--   <li>Cannot end with a hyphen or contain two consecutive hyphens</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:preferredBackupWindow:CreateDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>createDBInstance_preferredBackupWindow</a> - The daily time range
--   during which automated backups are created.
--   
--   Not applicable. The daily time range for creating automated backups is
--   managed by the DB cluster. For more information, see CreateDBCluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:availabilityZone:CreateDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>createDBInstance_availabilityZone</a> - The EC2 Availability Zone
--   that the DB instance is created in
--   
--   Default: A random, system-chosen Availability Zone in the endpoint's
--   Amazon Region.
--   
--   Example: <tt>us-east-1d</tt>
--   
--   Constraint: The AvailabilityZone parameter can't be specified if the
--   MultiAZ parameter is set to <tt>true</tt>. The specified Availability
--   Zone must be in the same Amazon Region as the current endpoint.
--   
--   <a>$sel:backupRetentionPeriod:CreateDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>createDBInstance_backupRetentionPeriod</a> - The number of days for
--   which automated backups are retained.
--   
--   Not applicable. The retention period for automated backups is managed
--   by the DB cluster. For more information, see CreateDBCluster.
--   
--   Default: 1
--   
--   Constraints:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Must be a value from 0 to 35</li>
--   <li>Cannot be set to 0 if the DB instance is a source to Read
--   Replicas</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:performanceInsightsKMSKeyId:CreateDBInstance'</a>,

--   supported by Neptune)</i>
--   
--   <a>$sel:vpcSecurityGroupIds:CreateDBInstance'</a>,

--   security groups to associate with this DB instance.
--   
--   Not applicable. The associated list of EC2 VPC security groups is
--   managed by the DB cluster. For more information, see CreateDBCluster.
--   
--   Default: The default EC2 VPC security group for the DB subnet group's
--   VPC.
--   
--   <a>$sel:multiAZ:CreateDBInstance'</a>, <a>createDBInstance_multiAZ</a>
--   - Specifies if the DB instance is a Multi-AZ deployment. You can't set
--   the AvailabilityZone parameter if the MultiAZ parameter is set to
--   true.
--   
--   <a>$sel:allocatedStorage:CreateDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>createDBInstance_allocatedStorage</a> - Not supported by Neptune.
--   
--   <a>$sel:optionGroupName:CreateDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>createDBInstance_optionGroupName</a> - <i>(Not supported by
--   Neptune)</i>
--   
--   <a>$sel:copyTagsToSnapshot:CreateDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>createDBInstance_copyTagsToSnapshot</a> - True to copy all tags
--   from the DB instance to snapshots of the DB instance, and otherwise
--   false. The default is false.
--   
--   <a>$sel:timezone:CreateDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>createDBInstance_timezone</a> - The time zone of the DB instance.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tdeCredentialArn:CreateDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>createDBInstance_tdeCredentialArn</a> - The ARN from the key store
--   with which to associate the instance for TDE encryption.
--   
--   <a>$sel:domainIAMRoleName:CreateDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>createDBInstance_domainIAMRoleName</a> - Specify the name of the
--   IAM role to be used when making API calls to the Directory Service.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tags:CreateDBInstance'</a>, <a>createDBInstance_tags</a> - The
--   tags to assign to the new instance.
--   
--   <a>$sel:port:CreateDBInstance'</a>, <a>createDBInstance_port</a> - The
--   port number on which the database accepts connections.
--   
--   Not applicable. The port is managed by the DB cluster. For more
--   information, see CreateDBCluster.
--   
--   Default: <tt>8182</tt>
--   
--   Type: Integer
--   
--   <a>$sel:enableIAMDatabaseAuthentication:CreateDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>createDBInstance_enableIAMDatabaseAuthentication</a> - Not

--   
--   <a>$sel:storageType:CreateDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>createDBInstance_storageType</a> - Specifies the storage type to be
--   associated with the DB instance.
--   
--   Not applicable. Storage is managed by the DB Cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:enableCloudwatchLogsExports:CreateDBInstance'</a>,

--   types that need to be enabled for exporting to CloudWatch Logs.

--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Must contain from 1 to 63 letters, numbers, or hyphens.</li>
--   <li>First character must be a letter.</li>
--   <li>Cannot end with a hyphen or contain two consecutive hyphens.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Example: <tt>mydbinstance</tt>
--

--   
--   The default is a 30-minute window selected at random from an 8-hour
--   block of time for each Amazon Region, occurring on a random day of the

--   modifications are asynchronously applied as soon as possible,
--   regardless of the <tt>PreferredMaintenanceWindow</tt> setting for the
--   DB cluster. If this parameter is set to <tt>false</tt>, changes to the
--   DB cluster are applied during the next maintenance window.

--   <tt>ApplyImmediately</tt> parameter value to false, then changes to

CopyDBClusterSnapshot' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Tag] -> Text -> Text -> CopyDBClusterSnapshot

-- | Create a value of <a>CopyDBClusterSnapshot</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:preSignedUrl:CopyDBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>copyDBClusterSnapshot_preSignedUrl</a> - Not currently supported.
--   
--   <a>$sel:copyTags:CopyDBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>copyDBClusterSnapshot_copyTags</a> - True to copy all tags from the
--   source DB cluster snapshot to the target DB cluster snapshot, and
--   otherwise false. The default is false.
--   
--   <a>$sel:kmsKeyId:CopyDBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>copyDBClusterSnapshot_kmsKeyId</a> - The Amazon Amazon KMS key ID
--   for an encrypted DB cluster snapshot. The KMS key ID is the Amazon
--   Resource Name (ARN), KMS key identifier, or the KMS key alias for the
--   KMS encryption key.
--   
--   If you copy an encrypted DB cluster snapshot from your Amazon account,
--   you can specify a value for <tt>KmsKeyId</tt> to encrypt the copy with
--   a new KMS encryption key. If you don't specify a value for
--   <tt>KmsKeyId</tt>, then the copy of the DB cluster snapshot is
--   encrypted with the same KMS key as the source DB cluster snapshot.
--   
--   If you copy an encrypted DB cluster snapshot that is shared from
--   another Amazon account, then you must specify a value for
--   <tt>KmsKeyId</tt>.
--   
--   KMS encryption keys are specific to the Amazon Region that they are
--   created in, and you can't use encryption keys from one Amazon Region
--   in another Amazon Region.
--   
--   You cannot encrypt an unencrypted DB cluster snapshot when you copy
--   it. If you try to copy an unencrypted DB cluster snapshot and specify
--   a value for the KmsKeyId parameter, an error is returned.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tags:CopyDBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>copyDBClusterSnapshot_tags</a> - The tags to assign to the new DB
--   cluster snapshot copy.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceDBClusterSnapshotIdentifier:CopyDBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>copyDBClusterSnapshot_sourceDBClusterSnapshotIdentifier</a> - The
--   identifier of the DB cluster snapshot to copy. This parameter is not
--   case-sensitive.
--   
--   Constraints:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Must specify a valid system snapshot in the "available"
--   state.</li>
--   <li>Specify a valid DB snapshot identifier.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Example: <tt>my-cluster-snapshot1</tt>
--   
--   <a>$sel:targetDBClusterSnapshotIdentifier:CopyDBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>copyDBClusterSnapshot_targetDBClusterSnapshotIdentifier</a> - The
--   identifier of the new DB cluster snapshot to create from the source DB
--   cluster snapshot. This parameter is not case-sensitive.
--   
--   Constraints:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Must contain from 1 to 63 letters, numbers, or hyphens.</li>
--   <li>First character must be a letter.</li>
--   <li>Cannot end with a hyphen or contain two consecutive hyphens.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Example: <tt>my-cluster-snapshot2</tt>

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:engineVersion:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_engineVersion</a> - The version number of the
--   database engine to use for the new DB cluster.
--   
--   Example: <tt>1.0.2.1</tt>
--   
--   <a>$sel:deletionProtection:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_deletionProtection</a> - A value that indicates
--   whether the DB cluster has deletion protection enabled. The database
--   can't be deleted when deletion protection is enabled. By default,
--   deletion protection is enabled.
--   
--   <a>$sel:storageEncrypted:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_storageEncrypted</a> - Specifies whether the DB
--   cluster is encrypted.
--   
--   <a>$sel:masterUserPassword:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_masterUserPassword</a> - Not supported by Neptune.
--   
--   <a>$sel:replicationSourceIdentifier:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_replicationSourceIdentifier</a> - The Amazon
--   Resource Name (ARN) of the source DB instance or DB cluster if this DB
--   cluster is created as a Read Replica.
--   
--   <a>$sel:masterUsername:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_masterUsername</a> - Not supported by Neptune.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbSubnetGroupName:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_dbSubnetGroupName</a> - A DB subnet group to
--   associate with this DB cluster.
--   
--   Constraints: Must match the name of an existing DBSubnetGroup. Must
--   not be default.
--   
--   Example: <tt>mySubnetgroup</tt>
--   
--   <a>$sel:preSignedUrl:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_preSignedUrl</a> - This parameter is not currently
--   supported.
--   
--   <a>$sel:preferredMaintenanceWindow:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_preferredMaintenanceWindow</a> - The weekly time
--   range during which system maintenance can occur, in Universal
--   Coordinated Time (UTC).
--   
--   Format: <tt>ddd:hh24:mi-ddd:hh24:mi</tt>
--   
--   The default is a 30-minute window selected at random from an 8-hour
--   block of time for each Amazon Region, occurring on a random day of the
--   week. To see the time blocks available, see <a>Adjusting the Preferred
--   Maintenance Window</a> in the <i>Amazon Neptune User Guide.</i>
--   
--   Valid Days: Mon, Tue, Wed, Thu, Fri, Sat, Sun.
--   
--   Constraints: Minimum 30-minute window.
--   
--   <a>$sel:availabilityZones:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_availabilityZones</a> - A list of EC2 Availability
--   Zones that instances in the DB cluster can be created in.
--   
--   <a>$sel:characterSetName:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_characterSetName</a> - <i>(Not supported by
--   Neptune)</i>
--   
--   <a>$sel:kmsKeyId:CreateDBCluster'</a>, <a>createDBCluster_kmsKeyId</a>
--   - The Amazon KMS key identifier for an encrypted DB cluster.
--   
--   The KMS key identifier is the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the KMS
--   encryption key. If you are creating a DB cluster with the same Amazon
--   account that owns the KMS encryption key used to encrypt the new DB
--   cluster, then you can use the KMS key alias instead of the ARN for the
--   KMS encryption key.
--   
--   If an encryption key is not specified in <tt>KmsKeyId</tt>:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>If <tt>ReplicationSourceIdentifier</tt> identifies an encrypted
--   source, then Amazon Neptune will use the encryption key used to
--   encrypt the source. Otherwise, Amazon Neptune will use your default
--   encryption key.</li>
--   <li>If the <tt>StorageEncrypted</tt> parameter is true and
--   <tt>ReplicationSourceIdentifier</tt> is not specified, then Amazon
--   Neptune will use your default encryption key.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Amazon KMS creates the default encryption key for your Amazon account.
--   Your Amazon account has a different default encryption key for each
--   Amazon Region.
--   
--   If you create a Read Replica of an encrypted DB cluster in another
--   Amazon Region, you must set <tt>KmsKeyId</tt> to a KMS key ID that is
--   valid in the destination Amazon Region. This key is used to encrypt
--   the Read Replica in that Amazon Region.
--   
--   <a>$sel:preferredBackupWindow:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_preferredBackupWindow</a> - The daily time range
--   during which automated backups are created if automated backups are
--   enabled using the <tt>BackupRetentionPeriod</tt> parameter.
--   
--   The default is a 30-minute window selected at random from an 8-hour
--   block of time for each Amazon Region. To see the time blocks
--   available, see <a>Adjusting the Preferred Maintenance Window</a> in
--   the <i>Amazon Neptune User Guide.</i>
--   
--   Constraints:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Must be in the format <tt>hh24:mi-hh24:mi</tt>.</li>
--   <li>Must be in Universal Coordinated Time (UTC).</li>
--   <li>Must not conflict with the preferred maintenance window.</li>
--   <li>Must be at least 30 minutes.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:backupRetentionPeriod:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_backupRetentionPeriod</a> - The number of days for
--   which automated backups are retained. You must specify a minimum value
--   of 1.
--   
--   Default: 1
--   
--   Constraints:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Must be a value from 1 to 35</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:vpcSecurityGroupIds:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_vpcSecurityGroupIds</a> - A list of EC2 VPC
--   security groups to associate with this DB cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:databaseName:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_databaseName</a> - The name for your database of up
--   to 64 alpha-numeric characters. If you do not provide a name, Amazon
--   Neptune will not create a database in the DB cluster you are creating.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbClusterParameterGroupName:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_dbClusterParameterGroupName</a> - The name of the
--   DB cluster parameter group to associate with this DB cluster. If this
--   argument is omitted, the default is used.
--   
--   Constraints:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>If supplied, must match the name of an existing
--   DBClusterParameterGroup.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:optionGroupName:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_optionGroupName</a> - <i>(Not supported by
--   Neptune)</i>
--   
--   <a>$sel:copyTagsToSnapshot:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_copyTagsToSnapshot</a> - /If set to <tt>true</tt>,
--   tags are copied to any snapshot of the DB cluster that is created./
--   
--   <a>$sel:tags:CreateDBCluster'</a>, <a>createDBCluster_tags</a> - The
--   tags to assign to the new DB cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:port:CreateDBCluster'</a>, <a>createDBCluster_port</a> - The
--   port number on which the instances in the DB cluster accept
--   connections.
--   
--   Default: <tt>8182</tt>
--   
--   <a>$sel:enableIAMDatabaseAuthentication:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_enableIAMDatabaseAuthentication</a> - If set to
--   <tt>true</tt>, enables Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM)
--   authentication for the entire DB cluster (this cannot be set at an
--   instance level).
--   
--   Default: <tt>false</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:enableCloudwatchLogsExports:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_enableCloudwatchLogsExports</a> - The list of log
--   types that need to be enabled for exporting to CloudWatch Logs.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbClusterIdentifier:CreateDBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>createDBCluster_dbClusterIdentifier</a> - The DB cluster
--   identifier. This parameter is stored as a lowercase string.
--   
--   Constraints:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Must contain from 1 to 63 letters, numbers, or hyphens.</li>
--   <li>First character must be a letter.</li>
--   <li>Cannot end with a hyphen or contain two consecutive hyphens.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Example: <tt>my-cluster1</tt>
--   
--   <a>$sel:engine:CreateDBCluster'</a>, <a>createDBCluster_engine</a> -
--   The name of the database engine to be used for this DB cluster.
--   
--   Valid Values: <tt>neptune</tt>

-- | Create a value of <a>DescribeDBClusterSnapshots</a> with all optional

--   DB cluster to retrieve the list of DB cluster snapshots for. This
--   parameter can't be used in conjunction with the
--   <tt>DBClusterSnapshotIdentifier</tt> parameter. This parameter is not
--   case-sensitive.
--   
--   Constraints:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>If supplied, must match the identifier of an existing
--   DBCluster.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:includeShared:DescribeDBClusterSnapshots'</a>,
--   <a>describeDBClusterSnapshots_includeShared</a> - True to include
--   shared manual DB cluster snapshots from other Amazon accounts that
--   this AWS account has been given permission to copy or restore, and
--   otherwise false. The default is <tt>false</tt>.
--   
--   You can give an Amazon account permission to restore a manual DB
--   cluster snapshot from another Amazon account by the
--   ModifyDBClusterSnapshotAttribute API action.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbClusterSnapshotIdentifier:DescribeDBClusterSnapshots'</a>,
--   <a>describeDBClusterSnapshots_dbClusterSnapshotIdentifier</a> - A
--   specific DB cluster snapshot identifier to describe. This parameter
--   can't be used in conjunction with the <tt>DBClusterIdentifier</tt>
--   parameter. This value is stored as a lowercase string.
--   
--   Constraints:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>If supplied, must match the identifier of an existing
--   DBClusterSnapshot.</li>
--   <li>If this identifier is for an automated snapshot, the
--   <tt>SnapshotType</tt> parameter must also be specified.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:filters:DescribeDBClusterSnapshots'</a>,
--   <a>describeDBClusterSnapshots_filters</a> - This parameter is not
--   currently supported.
--   
--   <a>$sel:snapshotType:DescribeDBClusterSnapshots'</a>,
--   <a>describeDBClusterSnapshots_snapshotType</a> - The type of DB
--   cluster snapshots to be returned. You can specify one of the following
--   values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>automated</tt> - Return all DB cluster snapshots that have
--   been automatically taken by Amazon Neptune for my Amazon account.</li>
--   <li><tt>manual</tt> - Return all DB cluster snapshots that have been
--   taken by my AWS account.</li>
--   <li><tt>shared</tt> - Return all manual DB cluster snapshots that have
--   been shared to my Amazon account.</li>
--   <li><tt>public</tt> - Return all DB cluster snapshots that have been
--   marked as public.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   If you don't specify a <tt>SnapshotType</tt> value, then both
--   automated and manual DB cluster snapshots are returned. You can
--   include shared DB cluster snapshots with these results by setting the
--   <tt>IncludeShared</tt> parameter to <tt>true</tt>. You can include
--   public DB cluster snapshots with these results by setting the
--   <tt>IncludePublic</tt> parameter to <tt>true</tt>.
--   
--   The <tt>IncludeShared</tt> and <tt>IncludePublic</tt> parameters don't
--   apply for <tt>SnapshotType</tt> values of <tt>manual</tt> or
--   <tt>automated</tt>. The <tt>IncludePublic</tt> parameter doesn't apply
--   when <tt>SnapshotType</tt> is set to <tt>shared</tt>. The
--   <tt>IncludeShared</tt> parameter doesn't apply when
--   <tt>SnapshotType</tt> is set to <tt>public</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:marker:DescribeDBClusterSnapshots'</a>,
--   <a>describeDBClusterSnapshots_marker</a> - An optional pagination
--   token provided by a previous <tt>DescribeDBClusterSnapshots</tt>
--   request. If this parameter is specified, the response includes only
--   records beyond the marker, up to the value specified by
--   <tt>MaxRecords</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:maxRecords:DescribeDBClusterSnapshots'</a>,

--   records to include in the response. If more records exist than the
--   specified <tt>MaxRecords</tt> value, a pagination token called a
--   marker is included in the response so that the remaining results can
--   be retrieved.
--   
--   Default: 100
--   
--   Constraints: Minimum 20, maximum 100.
--   
--   <a>$sel:includePublic:DescribeDBClusterSnapshots'</a>,
--   <a>describeDBClusterSnapshots_includePublic</a> - True to include
--   manual DB cluster snapshots that are public and can be copied or
--   restored by any Amazon account, and otherwise false. The default is
--   <tt>false</tt>. The default is false.
--   
--   You can share a manual DB cluster snapshot as public by using the
--   ModifyDBClusterSnapshotAttribute API action.
newDescribeDBClusterSnapshots :: DescribeDBClusterSnapshots

--   DBSnapshotIdentifier of the new DBSnapshot created when
--   SkipFinalSnapshot is set to <tt>false</tt>.
--   
--   Specifying this parameter and also setting the SkipFinalShapshot
--   parameter to true results in an error.
--   
--   Constraints:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Must be 1 to 255 letters or numbers.</li>
--   <li>First character must be a letter</li>
--   <li>Cannot end with a hyphen or contain two consecutive hyphens</li>
--   <li>Cannot be specified when deleting a Read Replica.</li>
--   </ul>

--   <a>$sel:skipFinalSnapshot:DeleteDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>deleteDBInstance_skipFinalSnapshot</a> - Determines whether a final
--   DB snapshot is created before the DB instance is deleted. If
--   <tt>true</tt> is specified, no DBSnapshot is created. If
--   <tt>false</tt> is specified, a DB snapshot is created before the DB
--   instance is deleted.
--   
--   Note that when a DB instance is in a failure state and has a status of
--   'failed', 'incompatible-restore', or 'incompatible-network', it can
--   only be deleted when the SkipFinalSnapshot parameter is set to "true".
--   
--   Specify <tt>true</tt> when deleting a Read Replica.
--   
--   The FinalDBSnapshotIdentifier parameter must be specified if
--   SkipFinalSnapshot is <tt>false</tt>.
--   
--   Default: <tt>false</tt>
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbInstanceIdentifier:DeleteDBInstance'</a>,
--   <a>deleteDBInstance_dbInstanceIdentifier</a> - The DB instance
--   identifier for the DB instance to be deleted. This parameter isn't
--   case-sensitive.
--   
--   Constraints:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Must match the name of an existing DB instance.</li>

data RestoreDBClusterToPointInTime

-- | Create a value of <a>RestoreDBClusterToPointInTime</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:deletionProtection:RestoreDBClusterToPointInTime'</a>,
--   <a>restoreDBClusterToPointInTime_deletionProtection</a> - A value that
--   indicates whether the DB cluster has deletion protection enabled. The
--   database can't be deleted when deletion protection is enabled. By
--   default, deletion protection is disabled.
--   
--   <a>$sel:useLatestRestorableTime:RestoreDBClusterToPointInTime'</a>,
--   <a>restoreDBClusterToPointInTime_useLatestRestorableTime</a> - A value
--   that is set to <tt>true</tt> to restore the DB cluster to the latest
--   restorable backup time, and <tt>false</tt> otherwise.
--   
--   Default: <tt>false</tt>
--   
--   Constraints: Cannot be specified if <tt>RestoreToTime</tt> parameter
--   is provided.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbSubnetGroupName:RestoreDBClusterToPointInTime'</a>,
--   <a>restoreDBClusterToPointInTime_dbSubnetGroupName</a> - The DB subnet
--   group name to use for the new DB cluster.
--   
--   Constraints: If supplied, must match the name of an existing
--   DBSubnetGroup.
--   
--   Example: <tt>mySubnetgroup</tt>
--   
--   <a>$sel:kmsKeyId:RestoreDBClusterToPointInTime'</a>,
--   <a>restoreDBClusterToPointInTime_kmsKeyId</a> - The Amazon KMS key
--   identifier to use when restoring an encrypted DB cluster from an
--   encrypted DB cluster.
--   
--   The KMS key identifier is the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the KMS
--   encryption key. If you are restoring a DB cluster with the same Amazon
--   account that owns the KMS encryption key used to encrypt the new DB
--   cluster, then you can use the KMS key alias instead of the ARN for the
--   KMS encryption key.
--   
--   You can restore to a new DB cluster and encrypt the new DB cluster
--   with a KMS key that is different than the KMS key used to encrypt the
--   source DB cluster. The new DB cluster is encrypted with the KMS key
--   identified by the <tt>KmsKeyId</tt> parameter.
--   
--   If you do not specify a value for the <tt>KmsKeyId</tt> parameter,
--   then the following will occur:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>If the DB cluster is encrypted, then the restored DB cluster is
--   encrypted using the KMS key that was used to encrypt the source DB
--   cluster.</li>
--   <li>If the DB cluster is not encrypted, then the restored DB cluster
--   is not encrypted.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   If <tt>DBClusterIdentifier</tt> refers to a DB cluster that is not
--   encrypted, then the restore request is rejected.
--   
--   <a>$sel:vpcSecurityGroupIds:RestoreDBClusterToPointInTime'</a>,
--   <a>restoreDBClusterToPointInTime_vpcSecurityGroupIds</a> - A list of
--   VPC security groups that the new DB cluster belongs to.
--   
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbClusterParameterGroupName:RestoreDBClusterToPointInTime'</a>,
--   <a>restoreDBClusterToPointInTime_dbClusterParameterGroupName</a> - The
--   name of the DB cluster parameter group to associate with the new DB
--   cluster.
--   
--   Constraints:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>If supplied, must match the name of an existing
--   DBClusterParameterGroup.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:restoreType:RestoreDBClusterToPointInTime'</a>,
--   <a>restoreDBClusterToPointInTime_restoreType</a> - The type of restore
--   to be performed. You can specify one of the following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>full-copy</tt> - The new DB cluster is restored as a full copy
--   of the source DB cluster.</li>
--   <li><tt>copy-on-write</tt> - The new DB cluster is restored as a clone
--   of the source DB cluster.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   If you don't specify a <tt>RestoreType</tt> value, then the new DB
--   cluster is restored as a full copy of the source DB cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:optionGroupName:RestoreDBClusterToPointInTime'</a>,
--   <a>restoreDBClusterToPointInTime_optionGroupName</a> - <i>(Not
--   supported by Neptune)</i>
--   
--   <a>$sel:restoreToTime:RestoreDBClusterToPointInTime'</a>,
--   <a>restoreDBClusterToPointInTime_restoreToTime</a> - The date and time
--   to restore the DB cluster to.
--   
--   Valid Values: Value must be a time in Universal Coordinated Time (UTC)
--   format
--   
--   Constraints:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Must be before the latest restorable time for the DB instance</li>
--   <li>Must be specified if <tt>UseLatestRestorableTime</tt> parameter is
--   not provided</li>
--   <li>Cannot be specified if <tt>UseLatestRestorableTime</tt> parameter
--   is true</li>
--   <li>Cannot be specified if <tt>RestoreType</tt> parameter is
--   <tt>copy-on-write</tt></li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Example: <tt>2015-03-07T23:45:00Z</tt>
--   
--   <a>$sel:tags:RestoreDBClusterToPointInTime'</a>,
--   <a>restoreDBClusterToPointInTime_tags</a> - The tags to be applied to
--   the restored DB cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:port:RestoreDBClusterToPointInTime'</a>,
--   <a>restoreDBClusterToPointInTime_port</a> - The port number on which
--   the new DB cluster accepts connections.
--   
--   Constraints: Value must be <tt>1150-65535</tt>
--   
--   Default: The same port as the original DB cluster.
--   
--   
--   <a>$sel:enableIAMDatabaseAuthentication:RestoreDBClusterToPointInTime'</a>,
--   <a>restoreDBClusterToPointInTime_enableIAMDatabaseAuthentication</a> -
--   True to enable mapping of Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM)
--   accounts to database accounts, and otherwise false.
--   
--   Default: <tt>false</tt>
--   
--   
--   <a>$sel:enableCloudwatchLogsExports:RestoreDBClusterToPointInTime'</a>,
--   <a>restoreDBClusterToPointInTime_enableCloudwatchLogsExports</a> - The
--   list of logs that the restored DB cluster is to export to CloudWatch
--   Logs.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbClusterIdentifier:RestoreDBClusterToPointInTime'</a>,
--   <a>restoreDBClusterToPointInTime_dbClusterIdentifier</a> - The name of
--   the new DB cluster to be created.
--   
--   Constraints:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Must contain from 1 to 63 letters, numbers, or hyphens</li>
--   <li>First character must be a letter</li>
--   <li>Cannot end with a hyphen or contain two consecutive hyphens</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceDBClusterIdentifier:RestoreDBClusterToPointInTime'</a>,

--   identifier of the source DB cluster from which to restore.
--   
--   Constraints:
--

--   marker, up to the value specified by <tt>MaxRecords</tt>.

--   
--   Default: 100
--

-- | Contains the details of an Amazon Neptune DB cluster.
--   
--   This data type is used as a response element in the DescribeDBClusters
--   action.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDBCluster</a> smart constructor.
data DBCluster

--   <a>dbCluster_vpcSecurityGroups</a> - Provides a list of VPC security

--   
--   <a>$sel:backupRetentionPeriod:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_backupRetentionPeriod</a> - Specifies the number of days

--   
--   <a>$sel:dbSubnetGroup:DBCluster'</a>, <a>dbCluster_dbSubnetGroup</a> -

--   cluster, including the name, description, and subnets in the subnet

--   provided at create time, if one was specified when the DB cluster was
--   created. This same name is returned for the life of the DB cluster.

--   <a>dbCluster_allocatedStorage</a> - <tt>AllocatedStorage</tt> always
--   returns 1, because Neptune DB cluster storage size is not fixed, but
--   instead automatically adjusts as needed.
--   
--   <a>$sel:copyTagsToSnapshot:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_copyTagsToSnapshot</a> - /If set to <tt>true</tt>, tags
--   are copied to any snapshot of the DB cluster that is created./

--   cluster was created, in Universal Coordinated Time (UTC).

--   the connection endpoint for the primary instance of the DB cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:percentProgress:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_percentProgress</a> - Specifies the progress of the
--   operation as a percentage.
--   
--   <a>$sel:readerEndpoint:DBCluster'</a>, <a>dbCluster_readerEndpoint</a>
--   - The reader endpoint for the DB cluster. The reader endpoint for a DB
--   cluster load-balances connections across the Read Replicas that are
--   available in a DB cluster. As clients request new connections to the
--   reader endpoint, Neptune distributes the connection requests among the
--   Read Replicas in the DB cluster. This functionality can help balance
--   your read workload across multiple Read Replicas in your DB cluster.
--   
--   If a failover occurs, and the Read Replica that you are connected to
--   is promoted to be the primary instance, your connection is dropped. To
--   continue sending your read workload to other Read Replicas in the
--   cluster, you can then reconnect to the reader endpoint.
--   
--   <a>$sel:port:DBCluster'</a>, <a>dbCluster_port</a> - Specifies the
--   port that the database engine is listening on.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbClusterOptionGroupMemberships:DBCluster'</a>,
--   <a>dbCluster_dbClusterOptionGroupMemberships</a> - Not supported by
--   Neptune.
newDBCluster :: DBCluster

--   - The current status of the endpoint. One of: <tt>creating</tt>,
--   <tt>available</tt>, <tt>deleting</tt>, <tt>inactive</tt>,
--   <tt>modifying</tt>. The <tt>inactive</tt> state applies to an endpoint
--   that cannot be used for a certain kind of cluster, such as a

-- | Describes an Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM) role that is
--   associated with a DB cluster.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDBClusterRole</a> smart constructor.
data DBClusterRole
DBClusterRole' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> DBClusterRole

-- | Create a value of <a>DBClusterRole</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:DBClusterRole'</a>, <a>dbClusterRole_status</a> -
--   Describes the state of association between the IAM role and the DB
--   cluster. The Status property returns one of the following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>ACTIVE</tt> - the IAM role ARN is associated with the DB
--   cluster and can be used to access other Amazon services on your
--   behalf.</li>
--   <li><tt>PENDING</tt> - the IAM role ARN is being associated with the
--   DB cluster.</li>
--   <li><tt>INVALID</tt> - the IAM role ARN is associated with the DB
--   cluster, but the DB cluster is unable to assume the IAM role in order
--   to access other Amazon services on your behalf.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:featureName:DBClusterRole'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterRole_featureName</a> - The name of the feature associated
--   with the Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM) role. For the
--   list of supported feature names, see DBEngineVersion.
--   
--   <a>$sel:roleArn:DBClusterRole'</a>, <a>dbClusterRole_roleArn</a> - The
--   Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the IAM role that is associated with the
--   DB cluster.
newDBClusterRole :: DBClusterRole

-- | Contains the details for an Amazon Neptune DB cluster snapshot
--   
--   This data type is used as a response element in the
--   DescribeDBClusterSnapshots action.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDBClusterSnapshot</a> smart constructor.
data DBClusterSnapshot
DBClusterSnapshot' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> DBClusterSnapshot

-- | Create a value of <a>DBClusterSnapshot</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:engineVersion:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshot_engineVersion</a> - Provides the version of the
--   database engine for this DB cluster snapshot.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>, <a>dbClusterSnapshot_status</a>
--   - Specifies the status of this DB cluster snapshot.
--   
--   <a>$sel:storageEncrypted:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshot_storageEncrypted</a> - Specifies whether the DB
--   cluster snapshot is encrypted.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbClusterIdentifier:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshot_dbClusterIdentifier</a> - Specifies the DB
--   cluster identifier of the DB cluster that this DB cluster snapshot was
--   created from.
--   
--   <a>$sel:masterUsername:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshot_masterUsername</a> - Not supported by Neptune.
--   
--   <a>$sel:iAMDatabaseAuthenticationEnabled:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshot_iAMDatabaseAuthenticationEnabled</a> - True if
--   mapping of Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM) accounts to
--   database accounts is enabled, and otherwise false.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbClusterSnapshotArn:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshot_dbClusterSnapshotArn</a> - The Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) for the DB cluster snapshot.
--   
--   <a>$sel:vpcId:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>, <a>dbClusterSnapshot_vpcId</a> -
--   Provides the VPC ID associated with the DB cluster snapshot.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dbClusterSnapshotIdentifier:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshot_dbClusterSnapshotIdentifier</a> - Specifies the
--   identifier for a DB cluster snapshot. Must match the identifier of an
--   existing snapshot.
--   
--   After you restore a DB cluster using a
--   <tt>DBClusterSnapshotIdentifier</tt>, you must specify the same
--   <tt>DBClusterSnapshotIdentifier</tt> for any future updates to the DB
--   cluster. When you specify this property for an update, the DB cluster
--   is not restored from the snapshot again, and the data in the database
--   is not changed.
--   
--   However, if you don't specify the
--   <tt>DBClusterSnapshotIdentifier</tt>, an empty DB cluster is created,
--   and the original DB cluster is deleted. If you specify a property that
--   is different from the previous snapshot restore property, the DB
--   cluster is restored from the snapshot specified by the
--   <tt>DBClusterSnapshotIdentifier</tt>, and the original DB cluster is
--   deleted.
--   
--   <a>$sel:engine:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>, <a>dbClusterSnapshot_engine</a>
--   - Specifies the name of the database engine.
--   
--   <a>$sel:licenseModel:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshot_licenseModel</a> - Provides the license model
--   information for this DB cluster snapshot.
--   
--   <a>$sel:availabilityZones:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshot_availabilityZones</a> - Provides the list of EC2
--   Availability Zones that instances in the DB cluster snapshot can be
--   restored in.
--   
--   <a>$sel:snapshotType:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshot_snapshotType</a> - Provides the type of the DB
--   cluster snapshot.
--   
--   <a>$sel:kmsKeyId:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshot_kmsKeyId</a> - If <tt>StorageEncrypted</tt> is
--   true, the Amazon KMS key identifier for the encrypted DB cluster
--   snapshot.
--   
--   <a>$sel:snapshotCreateTime:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshot_snapshotCreateTime</a> - Provides the time when
--   the snapshot was taken, in Universal Coordinated Time (UTC).
--   
--   <a>$sel:allocatedStorage:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshot_allocatedStorage</a> - Specifies the allocated
--   storage size in gibibytes (GiB).
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceDBClusterSnapshotArn:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshot_sourceDBClusterSnapshotArn</a> - If the DB
--   cluster snapshot was copied from a source DB cluster snapshot, the
--   Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the source DB cluster snapshot,
--   otherwise, a null value.
--   
--   <a>$sel:clusterCreateTime:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshot_clusterCreateTime</a> - Specifies the time when
--   the DB cluster was created, in Universal Coordinated Time (UTC).
--   
--   <a>$sel:percentProgress:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshot_percentProgress</a> - Specifies the percentage of
--   the estimated data that has been transferred.
--   
--   <a>$sel:port:DBClusterSnapshot'</a>, <a>dbClusterSnapshot_port</a> -
--   Specifies the port that the DB cluster was listening on at the time of
--   the snapshot.
newDBClusterSnapshot :: DBClusterSnapshot

-- | Contains the name and values of a manual DB cluster snapshot
--   attribute.
--   
--   Manual DB cluster snapshot attributes are used to authorize other
--   Amazon accounts to restore a manual DB cluster snapshot. For more
--   information, see the ModifyDBClusterSnapshotAttribute API action.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDBClusterSnapshotAttribute</a> smart constructor.
data DBClusterSnapshotAttribute
DBClusterSnapshotAttribute' :: Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> DBClusterSnapshotAttribute

-- | Create a value of <a>DBClusterSnapshotAttribute</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:attributeValues:DBClusterSnapshotAttribute'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshotAttribute_attributeValues</a> - The value(s) for
--   the manual DB cluster snapshot attribute.
--   
--   If the <tt>AttributeName</tt> field is set to <tt>restore</tt>, then
--   this element returns a list of IDs of the Amazon accounts that are
--   authorized to copy or restore the manual DB cluster snapshot. If a
--   value of <tt>all</tt> is in the list, then the manual DB cluster
--   snapshot is public and available for any Amazon account to copy or
--   restore.
--   
--   <a>$sel:attributeName:DBClusterSnapshotAttribute'</a>,
--   <a>dbClusterSnapshotAttribute_attributeName</a> - The name of the
--   manual DB cluster snapshot attribute.
--   
--   The attribute named <tt>restore</tt> refers to the list of Amazon
--   accounts that have permission to copy or restore the manual DB cluster
--   snapshot. For more information, see the
--   ModifyDBClusterSnapshotAttribute API action.
newDBClusterSnapshotAttribute :: DBClusterSnapshotAttribute

--   <a>$sel:fqdn:DomainMembership'</a>, <a>domainMembership_fqdn</a> - The
--   fully qualified domain name of the Active Directory Domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:domain:DomainMembership'</a>, <a>domainMembership_domain</a> -
--   The identifier of the Active Directory Domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:iAMRoleName:DomainMembership'</a>,
--   <a>domainMembership_iAMRoleName</a> - The name of the IAM role to be
--   used when making API calls to the Directory Service.
newDomainMembership :: DomainMembership

--   
--   Constraints:
--   
--   Can be one of the following: creating | modifying | deleting | active
--   | no-permission | topic-not-exist
--   
--   The status "no-permission" indicates that Neptune no longer has

--   indicates that the topic was deleted after the subscription was
--   created.

--   Name (ARN) for the event subscription.
--

--   subscription is enabled. True indicates the subscription is enabled.

data PendingCloudwatchLogsExports

--   optional fields omitted.

--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:logTypesToEnable:PendingCloudwatchLogsExports'</a>,

--   are in the process of being deactivated. After they are deactivated,
--   these log types aren't exported to CloudWatch Logs.
--   
--   <a>$sel:logTypesToDisable:PendingCloudwatchLogsExports'</a>,
--   <a>pendingCloudwatchLogsExports_logTypesToDisable</a> - Log types that
--   are in the process of being enabled. After they are enabled, these log
--   types are exported to CloudWatch Logs.
newPendingCloudwatchLogsExports :: PendingCloudwatchLogsExports

-- | Provides information about a pending maintenance action for a
--   resource.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newPendingMaintenanceAction</a> smart constructor.
data PendingMaintenanceAction
PendingMaintenanceAction' :: Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ISO8601 -> Maybe ISO8601 -> PendingMaintenanceAction

-- | Create a value of <a>PendingMaintenanceAction</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:autoAppliedAfterDate:PendingMaintenanceAction'</a>,
--   <a>pendingMaintenanceAction_autoAppliedAfterDate</a> - The date of the
--   maintenance window when the action is applied. The maintenance action
--   is applied to the resource during its first maintenance window after
--   this date. If this date is specified, any <tt>next-maintenance</tt>
--   opt-in requests are ignored.
--   
--   <a>$sel:action:PendingMaintenanceAction'</a>,
--   <a>pendingMaintenanceAction_action</a> - The type of pending
--   maintenance action that is available for the resource.
--   
--   <a>$sel:optInStatus:PendingMaintenanceAction'</a>,
--   <a>pendingMaintenanceAction_optInStatus</a> - Indicates the type of
--   opt-in request that has been received for the resource.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:PendingMaintenanceAction'</a>,
--   <a>pendingMaintenanceAction_description</a> - A description providing
--   more detail about the maintenance action.
--   
--   <a>$sel:forcedApplyDate:PendingMaintenanceAction'</a>,
--   <a>pendingMaintenanceAction_forcedApplyDate</a> - The date when the
--   maintenance action is automatically applied. The maintenance action is
--   applied to the resource on this date regardless of the maintenance
--   window for the resource. If this date is specified, any
--   <tt>immediate</tt> opt-in requests are ignored.
--   
--   <a>$sel:currentApplyDate:PendingMaintenanceAction'</a>,
--   <a>pendingMaintenanceAction_currentApplyDate</a> - The effective date
--   when the pending maintenance action is applied to the resource. This
--   date takes into account opt-in requests received from the
--   ApplyPendingMaintenanceAction API, the <tt>AutoAppliedAfterDate</tt>,
--   and the <tt>ForcedApplyDate</tt>. This value is blank if an opt-in
--   request has not been received and nothing has been specified as
--   <tt>AutoAppliedAfterDate</tt> or <tt>ForcedApplyDate</tt>.
newPendingMaintenanceAction :: PendingMaintenanceAction

-- | A range of integer values.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newRange</a> smart constructor.
data Range
Range' :: Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Range

-- | Create a value of <a>Range</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:to:Range'</a>, <a>range_to</a> - The maximum value in the
--   range.
--   
--   <a>$sel:from:Range'</a>, <a>range_from</a> - The minimum value in the
--   range.
--   
--   <a>$sel:step:Range'</a>, <a>range_step</a> - The step value for the
--   range. For example, if you have a range of 5,000 to 10,000, with a
--   step value of 1,000, the valid values start at 5,000 and step up by
--   1,000. Even though 7,500 is within the range, it isn't a valid value
--   for the range. The valid values are 5,000, 6,000, 7,000, 8,000...
newRange :: Range

-- | Describes the pending maintenance actions for a resource.

-- | Create a value of <a>Tag</a> with all optional fields omitted.

--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:value:Tag'</a>, <a>tag_value</a> - A value is the optional
--   value of the tag. The string value can be from 1 to 256 Unicode
--   characters in length and can't be prefixed with "aws:" or "rds:". The
--   string can only contain only the set of Unicode letters, digits,
--   white-space, '_', '.', '/', '=', '+', '-' (Java regex:
--   "^([\\p{L}\\p{Z}\\p{N}_.:/=+\\-]*)$").
--   
--   <a>$sel:key:Tag'</a>, <a>tag_key</a> - A key is the required name of
--   the tag. The string value can be from 1 to 128 Unicode characters in
--   length and can't be prefixed with "aws:" or "rds:". The string can
--   only contain only the set of Unicode letters, digits, white-space,
--   '_', '.', '/', '=', '+', '-' (Java regex:
--   "^([\\p{L}\\p{Z}\\p{N}_.:/=+\\-]*)$").

-- | The version of the database engine that a DB instance can be upgraded
--   to.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newUpgradeTarget</a> smart constructor.

-- | Create a value of <a>UpgradeTarget</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:engineVersion:UpgradeTarget'</a>,
--   <a>upgradeTarget_engineVersion</a> - The version number of the upgrade
--   target database engine.
--   
--   <a>$sel:isMajorVersionUpgrade:UpgradeTarget'</a>,
--   <a>upgradeTarget_isMajorVersionUpgrade</a> - A value that indicates
--   whether a database engine is upgraded to a major version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:engine:UpgradeTarget'</a>, <a>upgradeTarget_engine</a> - The
--   name of the upgrade target database engine.
--   
--   <a>$sel:autoUpgrade:UpgradeTarget'</a>,
--   <a>upgradeTarget_autoUpgrade</a> - A value that indicates whether the
--   target version is applied to any source DB instances that have
--   AutoMinorVersionUpgrade set to true.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:UpgradeTarget'</a>,
--   <a>upgradeTarget_description</a> - The version of the database engine
--   that a DB instance can be upgraded to.
newUpgradeTarget :: UpgradeTarget

-- | Information about valid modifications that you can make to your DB
--   instance.
--   
--   Contains the result of a successful call to the
--   DescribeValidDBInstanceModifications action.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newValidStorageOptions</a> smart constructor.
data ValidStorageOptions
ValidStorageOptions' :: Maybe [Range] -> Maybe [Range] -> Maybe [DoubleRange] -> Maybe Text -> ValidStorageOptions

-- | Create a value of <a>ValidStorageOptions</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:storageSize:ValidStorageOptions'</a>,
--   <a>validStorageOptions_storageSize</a> - The valid range of storage in
--   gibibytes. For example, 100 to 16384.
--   
--   <a>$sel:provisionedIops:ValidStorageOptions'</a>,
--   <a>validStorageOptions_provisionedIops</a> - The valid range of
--   provisioned IOPS. For example, 1000-20000.
--   
--   <a>$sel:iopsToStorageRatio:ValidStorageOptions'</a>,
--   <a>validStorageOptions_iopsToStorageRatio</a> - The valid range of
--   Provisioned IOPS to gibibytes of storage multiplier. For example,
--   3-10, which means that provisioned IOPS can be between 3 and 10 times
--   storage.
--   
--   <a>$sel:storageType:ValidStorageOptions'</a>,
--   <a>validStorageOptions_storageType</a> - The valid storage types for
--   your DB instance. For example, gp2, io1.
newValidStorageOptions :: ValidStorageOptions
